{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/23001667-murder-offstage", "title": "Murder Offstage", "titleComplete": "Murder Offstage (Posie Parker Mystery, #1)", "description": "Like your mysteries cozy and set during the Golden Age of Crime? This is the first book in the Posie Parker mysteries, although this novel can be enjoyed as a stand-alone story in its own right. Set in London in 1921, 'Murder Offstage' is full of intrigue and red herrings. This is a classic murder mystery which will appeal to fans of Agatha Christie and Downton Abbey.When Posie Parker\u2019s childhood friend is robbed of a priceless jewel and becomes a suspect in a cold-blooded murder case, budding detective Posie vows she will clear his name. Aided by her seriously gorgeous assistant Len, Posie soon realizes things are not quite as they seem, and the darkly-glamorous world of London\u2019s theatre and glittering nightclubs prove far more dangerous than she ever could have imagined.Just who exactly is the dangerous Lucky Lucy Gibson? And who is it she has killed in the lobby of the Ritz Hotel? And more importantly, what on earth has happened to Mr Minks, the much-loved office cat?", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1408511508i/23001667.jpg", "genres": ["Audiobook", "Amazon", "Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Historical", "Mystery Thriller", "Historical Fiction", "Historical Mystery", "Crime"], "asin": "B00LDWEXDO", "isbn": "0992925401", "publisher": "Whitehaven Man Press", "series": ["Posie Parker Mystery"], "author": ["L.B. Hathaway"], "publishDate": 1403938800000, "places": ["London, England"], "ratingHistogram": [76, 272, 1123, 1684, 1210], "ratingsCount": 4365, "reviewsCount": 381, "numPages": 278, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/30251834-hamburgers-homicide-and-a-honeymoon", "title": "Hamburgers, Homicide and a Honeymoon", "titleComplete": "Hamburgers, Homicide and a Honeymoon (Charlotte Denver #5)", "description": "What happens when small-town murder meets a big-hearted caf\u00e9 owner? When a belated honeymoon to London intertwines with an international tattoo awards ceremony, things takes a horrific turn when a celebration with new friends abruptly ends with the untimely death of one of the guests. Twists, turns, and red herrings are around every corner as the investigation into the death gathers pace and, as Charlotte and Nathan look forward to the birth of their first child back in St. Eves, the race is on to find a killer before the arrival of baby Costello. Charlotte and the rest of the St Eves gang are back in this mystery, set in St. Eves and London. A light, clean, fun, cozy mystery, with characters who'll stay with you long after you've finished reading, and recipes to try for yourself. You won't find any gore, graphic language, violence, sex, or cliffhangers in this book, but you will find a very happy ending! This book is written in British English and contains UK terminology and spelling.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1463934089i/30251834.jpg", "genres": ["Cozy Mystery"], "asin": "B01G0NC0VM", "series": ["Charlotte Denver"], "author": ["Sherri Bryan"], "publishDate": 1463814000000, "ratingHistogram": [1, 3, 17, 52, 130], "ratingsCount": 203, "reviewsCount": 11, "numPages": 240, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/26931783-engaged-in-death", "title": "Engaged in Death", "titleComplete": "Engaged in Death (Wedding Planner Mystery #1)", "description": "\"Had me in its spell from page one. Readers will love this.\" --Leslie MeierAll appears peaceful in sleepy Port Quincy, Pennsylvania--but in this small town, old grudges die hard. . .After dumping her cheating fianc\u00e9 and cancelling the wedding, Mallory Shepard can't bear another disaster. So when the former bride-to-be unexpectedly inherits Thistle Park, a ramshackle mansion in her ex's hometown of Port Quincy, it's a problem she can't afford--literally. Abound with stray cats, peeling wallpaper, and nosy neighbors, Mallory is dying to sell it off--once she finally fixes up both the place and her messy life. . .Turns out, Thistle Park has its charms. But the honeymoon phase is abruptly cut short when an unwanted visitor is found dead on the front lawn. Enlisting the help of her sister Rachel, Mallory vows to unveil the killer before she herself becomes married to the suspect list. . .\"I had great fun reading the adventures of nouveau sleuth Mallory Shepard as she wrangles corpses, kittens, and a cheating fianc\u00e9 in this charming debut mystery.\" --Laura Levine, author of Death by Tiara", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1445791866i/26931783.jpg", "genres": ["Audiobook", "Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Mystery Thriller", "Chick Lit", "Romance", "Crime", "Adult", "Contemporary"], "asin": "1496704789", "isbn": "1496704789", "isbn13": "9781496704788", "publisher": "Kensington", "series": ["Wedding Planner Mystery"], "author": ["Stephanie Blackmoore"], "publishDate": 1467097200000, "ratingHistogram": [10, 26, 262, 549, 378], "ratingsCount": 1225, "reviewsCount": 237, "numPages": 352, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/304605.Murder_la_Mode", "title": "Murder \u00e0 la Mode", "titleComplete": "Murder \u00e0 la Mode (Savannah Reid, #10)", "description": "Voluptuous P.I. Savannah Reid's culinary cravings come second only to her appetite for adventure. Of course, every girl needs a little down time, and Savannah adores curling up with a box of chocolates, a steaming Irish coffee, and an even steamier romance novel--preferably one with sexy Lance Roman on the cover. But when she meets her dream hunk in person, things take a decidedly nightmarish turn. . .As a special birthday treat, Savannah's friends have arranged for her to compete for Lance's affections on a reality TV show called Man of My Dreams. She and four other women will be living in a medieval \"castle\" with Lance, trying to win his heart.Unfortunately, the antics take a sinister turn when one of the show's producers, Tess Jarvis, turns up dead. It appears she was felled by a carton of Killer Fudge ice cream, but Savannah's convinced there's more to the story.Turns out she's right. It seems no one liked Tess. . .not her unhappy husband, or the scheming contestants, or all the disgruntled employees she so heinously wronged. This show is quickly turning into the worst kind of soap opera--with some footage that'll never make it on the air. . .\"Added to a well-plotted mystery, the very funny depiction of a different side of reality television makes Murder \u00e1 la Mode a delight.\"-- Mystery Scene\"Savannah retains her buoyant good humor throughout.\"-- Publishers Weekly", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388230802i/304605.jpg", "genres": ["Audiobook", "Murder Mystery", "Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Chick Lit"], "asin": "0758204612", "isbn": "0758204612", "isbn13": "9780758204615", "publisher": "Kensington", "series": ["A Savannah Reid Mystery"], "author": ["G.A. McKevett"], "publishDate": 1143878400000, "