{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/149345.Mrs_Pollifax_and_the_Whirling_Dervish", "title": "Mrs. Pollifax and the Whirling Dervish", "titleComplete": "Mrs. Pollifax and the Whirling Dervish (Mrs. Pollifax, #9)", "description": "All Mrs. Pollifax has to do is to masquerade as the aunt of an inept CIA representative while he confirms the identities of seven undercover agents in Morocco\u2014and keep him from making an unpleasant ass of himself. Immediately, things go horribly wrong. The first informant is murdered minutes after Mrs. Pollifax and her companion identify him in his brassware stall in Fez. Worse, she senses that her colleague is not who\u2014or what\u2014he says he is.With no one to bail her out, Mrs. Pollifax determines to outfox the enemy and check out the remaining informants on her own. Only Mrs. Pollifax would expose herself to the dangers of being an American and a woman alone in Morocco. And only she would forge ahead, knowing as she does that one of the original informants has been replaced by a deadly imposter...", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1395173075i/149345.jpg", "genres": ["Audiobook", "Cozy Mystery", "Adventure", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Espionage", "Mystery Thriller", "Thriller", "Suspense", "Africa"], "asin": "0449147606", "isbn": "0449147606", "isbn13": "9780449147603", "publisher": "Ballantine Fawcett Gold Medal", "series": ["Mrs. Pollifax"], "author": ["Dorothy Gilman"], "publishDate": 683708400000, "characters": ["Mrs. Emily Pollifax"], "places": ["Morocco"], "ratingHistogram": [14, 88, 1148, 2064, 1664], "ratingsCount": 4978, "reviewsCount": 294, "numPages": 211, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/16153431-deadly-devotion", "title": "Deadly Devotion", "titleComplete": "Deadly Devotion (Port Aster Secrets, #1)", "description": "Research scientist Kate Adams and her colleague Daisy are on the brink of a breakthrough for treating depression with herbal medicine when Daisy suddenly dies. Kate knows that if it hadn\u2019t been for Daisy\u2019s mentorship, she wouldn\u2019t have the job she loves or the faith she clings to. So when police rule Daisy\u2019s death a suicide, Kate is determined to unearth the truth.Former FBI agent Tom Parker finds it hard to adjust to life back in his hometown of Port Aster. Though an old buddy gives him a job as a detective on the local police force, not everyone approves. Tom\u2019s just trying to keep a low profile, so when Kate Adams demands he reopen the investigation of her friend\u2019s death, he knows his job is at stake. In fact, despite his attraction to her, Tom thinks Kate looks a bit suspicious herself.As evidence mounts, a web of intrigue is woven around the sleepy town of Port Aster. Can Kate uncover the truth? Or will Tom stand in her way?", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1353098154i/16153431.jpg", "genres": ["Christian Fiction", "Mystery", "Fiction", "Romantic Suspense", "Mystery Thriller", "Suspense", "Adult", "Romance", "Contemporary", "Christian"], "asin": "0800722221", "isbn": "0800722221", "isbn13": "9780800722227", "publisher": "Revell Books", "series": ["Port Aster Secrets"], "author": ["Sandra Orchard"], "publishDate": 1370070000000, "ratingHistogram": [35, 65, 302, 489, 460], "ratingsCount": 1351, "reviewsCount": 183, "numPages": 384, "language": "English"}
