{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/36680952-coffee-kids-and-a-kidnapping", "title": "Coffee, Kids, and a Kidnapping", "titleComplete": "Coffee, Kids, and a Kidnapping (Charlotte Ritter, #1)", "description": "Charlotte Ritter is a survivor and so much more. As a highly caffeinated go-getter busy raising three teenage kids on her own while juggling a full-time job at a family law practice, Charlotte has always dealt with things one day and one cup of coffee at a time. It\u2019s not always easy, especially with a highly autistic teenager and a new, snarky paralegal that was recently hired at the firm, but she manages. Then one day her average but hectic life gets turned upside down when her boss asks her to do some simple research for an adoption case. Charlotte\u2019s talent for connecting dots that most people don\u2019t see, leads her to believe there may have been an abduction that no one even knows about. Has she gone off the deep end or is she right and two people\u2019s lives may be at stake? The only person who believes her is her close friend and co-worker Cole. The deeper the unlikely pair look for the truth, the worse things seem to get as Charlotte\u2019s tenacity leads them down a very dangerous path. Pour yourself a cup of your favorite coffee and check out the first case in the Charlotte Ritter Cozy Mysteries.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1511909402i/36680952.jpg", "genres": ["Fiction", "Cozy Mystery", "Mystery", "Contemporary"], "series": ["Charlotte Ritter"], "author": ["Alyssa Helton"], "publishDate": 1511769600000, "ratingHistogram": [1, 8, 20, 34, 68], "ratingsCount": 131, "reviewsCount": 25, "numPages": 122, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/38145179-murder-at-kensington-gardens", "title": "Murder at Kensington Gardens", "titleComplete": "Murder at Kensington Gardens (Ginger Gold Mysteries #5)", "description": "\n  Murder's not a walk in the park . . .\n  \nWar widow fashionista, Ginger Gold, makes a gruesome discovery while walking her dog, Boss, through Kensington Gardens. A woman of ill-repute is dead.When Chief Inspector Basil Reed becomes a prime suspect, the blustery and often times pigheaded Superintendent Morris pulls him off the case. Ginger's not about to be pushed around by the superintendent, and investigates the case on her own--taking her into the spicy world of burlesque dancers--despite his warnings: if she doesn't butt out, she'll be arrested for impeding a police investigation.Despite Ginger and Basil's strained friendship, they agree to work together to find the killer. It's a proposition neither one may survive.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1516709706i/38145179.jpg", "genres": ["Audiobook", "Murder Mystery", "Cozy Mystery", "British Literature", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Historical", "Historical Fiction", "Historical Mystery", "Crime"], "publisher": "La Plume Press", "series": ["Ginger Gold Mysteries"], "author": ["Lee Strauss"], "publishDate": 1521529200000, "ratingHistogram": [17, 49, 438, 1017, 1218], "ratingsCount": 2739, "reviewsCount": 183, "numPages": 270, "language": "English"}
