{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3222778-six-geese-a-slaying", "title": "Six Geese A-Slaying", "titleComplete": "Six Geese A-Slaying (Meg Langslow, #10)", "description": "Meg and Michael\u2019s house is serving as the marshaling point for the annual Caerphilly Christmas parade. The theme is \u201cThe Twelve Days of Christmas,\u201d\u00a0and it features\u00a0twelve drummers from the school marching band, eleven\u00a0bagpipers, ten leaping lords costumed in medieval finery from the college drama department, etc. There are also assorted Christmas-themed floats, a live nativity scene on a flatbed truck, the Three Wise Men on Caerphilly zoo camels, and Santa Claus in a bright red horse-drawn sleigh (eight reindeer were beyond the zoo\u2019s scope).Meg has been volunteered to organize the parade, which is to proceed from her house to the local campus, where Santa will take up residence to hear the Christmas wishes of the town\u2019s children. Of course, getting all the camels, pipers, leapers, and drummers in order is proving every bit as difficult as Meg feared it would be. Then her nephew Eric, wide-eyed and ashen-faced, whispers, \u201cMeg, something\u2019s wrong with Santa.\u201dThe local curmudgeon, whose beard and belly made him a natural for the role, has been murdered. Now Meg and Chief Burke, who is playing one of the wise men, are faced with the two-fold mission of solving the murder and saving Christmas!Readers can look forward to another zany Meg Langslow mystery---this one filled with outrageous Christmas spirit\u2026and mayhem.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1431067316i/3222778.jpg", "genres": ["Christmas", "Holiday", "Audiobook", "Cozy Mystery", "Mystery", "Fiction", "Romance", "Humor", "Animals", "Adult"], "asin": "0312536100", "isbn": "0312536100", "isbn13": "9780312536107", "publisher": "Minotaur Books", "series": ["Meg Langslow"], "author": ["Donna Andrews"], "publishDate"