{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17166220-the-vanishing-thief", "title": "The Vanishing Thief", "titleComplete": "The Vanishing Thief (Victorian Bookshop Mystery #1)", "description": "1800s London. At 30, bookshop owner Georgia Fenchurch knows she\u2019s considered a middle-class old maid. To rescue people and see justice done, she works with the Archivist Society, too busy to be lonely.When a respectable middle-class woman comes into her bookshop complaining that handsome Duke of Blackford has abducted her next door neighbor, Georgia is embroiled in theft, blackmail, lies, secret marriages, and murder. Drake may be royalty, may be dead, and is definitely missing. Georgia also sees a man she has wanted to capture for a dozen years, he killed her parents.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1385354043i/17166220.jpg", "genres": ["Books About Books", "Cozy Mystery", "British Literature", "Mystery", "Fiction", "Historical", "Victorian", "Historical Fiction", "Historical Mystery", "Adult"], "asin": "0425266605", "isbn": "0425266605", "isbn13": "9780425266601", "publisher": "Berkley Prime Crime Penguin Random House", "series": ["Victorian Bookshop Mystery"], "author": ["Kate   Parker"], "publishDate": 1386057600000, "ratingHistogram": [32, 103, 387, 685, 619], "ratingsCount": 1826, "reviewsCount": 180, "numPages": 296, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/25845800-the-perfectly-proper-paranormal-museum", "title": "The Perfectly Proper Paranormal Museum", "titleComplete": "The Perfectly Proper Paranormal Museum (Perfectly Proper Paranormal Museum #1)", "description": "When Maddie Kosloski\u2019s career flatlines, she retreats to her wine-country hometown for solace and cheap rent. Railroaded into managing the local paranormal museum, she\u2019s certain the rumors of its haunting are greatly exaggerated. But a new ghost may be on the loose. A fresh corpse in the museum embroils Maddie in murders past and present.With her high school bully as one of the officers in charge, Maddie doubts justice will be served. When one of her best friends is arrested, she\u2019s certain it won\u2019t be.Maddie grapples with ghost hunters, obsessed taxidermists, and the sexy motorcyclist next door as outside forces threaten. And as she juggles spectral shenanigans with the hunt for a killer, she discovers there truly is no place like home.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1496845714i/25845800.jpg", "genres": ["Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Paranormal", "Mystery Thriller", "Ghosts", "Romance", "Supernatural", "Fantasy", "Contemporary"], "asin": "0738747513", "isbn": "0738747513", "isbn13": "9780738747514", "publisher": "Midnight Ink", "series": ["Perfectly Proper Paranormal Museum"], "author": ["Kirsten Weiss"], "publishDate": 1457424000000, "ratingHistogram": [34, 132, 771, 1367, 1196], "ratingsCount": 3500, "reviewsCount": 482, "numPages": 288, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/12716434-moord-kost-tijd", "title": "Moord kost tijd", "titleComplete": "Moord kost tijd", "description": "Who would kill the perfect gentleman?When Ernest Fletcher is found bludgeoned to death in his study, everyone is shocked and mystified: Ernest was well liked and respected, so who would have a motive for killing him? Inspectors of Scotland Yard felt it was an unlikely crime for the London suburbs: a perfectly respectable chap at home with his head bashed in. It seems the real Fletcher was far from the gentleman he pretended to be. There is, in fact, no shortage of people who wanted him dead.Superintendent Hannasyde and Sergeant Hemingway, with consummate skill, uncover one dirty little secret after another, and with them, a host of people who all have reasons for wanting Fletcher dead. Who tiptoed into the study to do the deed? The rather nefarious nephew Neville? A neighbor's wandering wife? A fat man in a bowler hat?The mystery's key was a blunt instrument--a weapon that the police could not find... and that the murderer can to use once more. Then, a second murder is committed, with striking similarities to the first, giving a grotesque twist to a very unusual case, and the inspectors realize they are up against a killer on a mission....", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1316941784i/12716434.jpg", "genres": ["Detective", "British Literature", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Historical", "Mystery Thriller", "Historical Fiction", "Romance", "Classics", "Crime"], "isbn": "9020520520", "publisher": "Westfriesland", "series": ["Inspectors Hannasyde & Hemingway"], "author": ["Georgette Heyer", "Jan Louwen"], "publishDate": 631180800000, "characters": ["Neville Fletcher", "Inspector Hemingway", "Sally Drew", "Inspector Hannasyde"], "ratingHistogram": [109, 309, 1201, 1418, 1152], "ratingsCount": 4189, "reviewsCount": 359, "numPages": 205, "language": "Dutch; Flemis