{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/55598103-beauty-expos-are-murder", "title": "Beauty Expos Are Murder", "titleComplete": "Beauty Expos Are Murder (A Poppy McAllister Mystery, #6)", "description": "Fans of Jana DeLeon and Joanne Fluke will love Libby Klein!\u00a0 Gluten-free baker Poppy McAllister is about to see the ugly side of beauty expos...Easter weekend on the Jersey Shore is hopping. Poppy's Bed and Breakfast is busier than ever, but she needs to leave things in the hopefully capable hands of Aunt Ginny--and paws of Figaro the black smoke Persian. She's selling her paleo muffins and keto cookies at the Health and Beauty Expo in Cape May's Convention Hall. Normally sharing a booth with the love of her life would be a treat, but she's recently discovered secrets that throw her new romance into chaos.But more secrets are about to be exposed at the expo. In his keynote address, prominent cosmetic surgeon Dr. Lance Rubin reveals his breakthrough anti-aging technology. Unfortunately, someone has one-upped him with a truly foolproof anti-aging murder. With the plastic surgeon dead under his own UV mask, and bedlam reigning in the hall and back at the B&amp;B, Poppy needs to follow a twisted trail marked by glowing footprints to unmask a killer...", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1602567950i/55598103.jpg", "genres": ["Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Mystery Thriller", "Cats", "Humor", "Contemporary"], "asin": "1496733134", "isbn": "1496733134", "isbn13": "9781496733139", "publisher": "Kensington", "series": ["A Poppy McAllister Mystery"], "author": ["Libby Klein"], "publishDate": 1624950000000, "ratingHistogram": [2, 2, 57, 171, 279], "ratingsCount": 511, "reviewsCount": 122, "numPages": 464, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/50848176-a-sprinkling-of-murder", "title": "A Sprinkling of Murder", "titleComplete": "A Sprinkling of Murder (A Fairy Garden Mystery #1)", "description": "Featured on Buzzfeed Books!\n  Fairy garden store owner Courtney Kelly believes in inviting magic into your life. But when uninvited trouble enters her shop, she'll need more than a sprinkling of her imagination to solve a murder . . . \n   Since childhood, Courtney has loved fairies. After her mother died when Courtney was ten, she lost touch with that feeling of magic. A year ago, at age twenty-nine, she rediscovered it when she left her father's landscaping business to spread her wings and start a fairy garden business and teashop in beautiful Carmel, California. At Open Your Imagination, she teaches garden design and sells everything from fairy figurines to tinkling wind chimes. Now she's starting a book club tea.But the light of the magical world she's created inside her shop is darkened one night when she discovers neighboring dog-grooming business owner Mick Watkins dead beside her patio fountain. To make matters worse, the police suspect Courtney of the crime. To clear her name and find the real killer, Courtney will have to wing it. But she's about to get a little help from an unexpected source . . .", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1580199979i/50848176.jpg", "genres": ["Audiobook", "Cozy Mystery", "Magic", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Paranormal", "Fairies", "Magical Realism", "Fantasy", "Contemporary"], "asin": "1496726340", "isbn": "1496726340", "isbn13": "9781496726346", "publisher": "Kensington Publishing Corporation", "series": ["A Fairy Garden Mystery"], "author": ["Daryl Wood Gerber"], "publishDate": 1593500400000, "places": ["Carmel-by-the-Sea, California"], "ratingHistogram": [20, 87, 325, 496, 363], "ratingsCount": 1291, "reviewsCount": 386, "numPages": 338, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/8749827-death-by-a-honeybee", "title": "Death By A HoneyBee", "titleComplete": "Death By A HoneyBee (Josiah Reynolds Mysteries, #1)", "description": "Josiah Reynolds, a former art history professor, was once a celebrity with wealth, social position, and a famous husband. Now all of that is gone. The professor finds her circumstances drastically altered. Josiah is now a full time beekeeper trying to stay financially afloat by selling honey at the local farmers market.She finds her world turned upside down when a man is found dead in her bee yard, only to discover the victim is her competitor and nemesis. The police suspect the brutal death is murder, and Josiah is their number one suspect.She is determined to find out who is trying to frame her, along with her assistant, Matt, who is twenty years her junior and gay, and her lawyer, Shaneika, an African-American woman, rumored to be a descendant of a historically prominent Lexington family. Josiah's powerful but secretive daughter pops in and out of her mother s life, pulling strings to protect her mother from danger.Set in the beautiful horse country of the Bluegrass, Josiah makes the rounds of quirky characters that can only be found in Kentucky. Fighting an unseen enemy in the glamorous world of Thoroughbreds, oak-cured bourbon, and antebellum plantation houses, Josiah struggles to uncover the truth in a city that keeps its secrets well.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1421711470i/8749827.jpg", "genres": ["Murder Mystery", "Amazon", "Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Thriller", "Mystery Thriller", "Suspense", "Crime", "Contemporary"], "asin": "0615347347", "publisher": "Worker Bee Press", "series": ["Josiah Reynolds Mysteries"], "author": ["Abigail Keam"], "publishDate": 1269327600000, "places": ["Kentucky"], "ratingHistogram": [153, 493, 1617, 1677, 1067], "ratingsCount": 5007, "reviewsCount": 568,