{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/39844835-day-of-the-dead", "title": "Day of the Dead: A Navajo Nation Mystery", "titleComplete": "Day of the Dead: A Navajo Nation Mystery", "description": "Tressa Tarango\u2019s husband lost his soul somewhere on the cold high desert of the Navajo Reservation. She doesn't know who killed him and only by venturing among warring drug cartels can she exact the revenge to pacify his restless soul. Only she can ensure Luca\u2019s troubled spirit finds peace in the underworld. Though his murderous rampage will keep him from heaven\u2014Tressa hopes she might yet secure him a higher place in hell. The dead have secrets yet to tell, and in the mysterious world of the desert southwest, no writer tells them better than Chappell. With a rock solid grip on the people, history and lives of the Din\u00e9, Chappell now leads the reader further into a world of mystery and intrigue as two powerful cultures clash. And while the spirit of a serial killer whispers to Tressa Tarango, Paul T'Sosi finds himself suspended between life and death\u2014and with only one old friend to rescue him from the darker forces of both the real and ethereal world. R. Allen Chappell's gripping Day Of The Dead, the 8th in his Navajo Nation Mystery series, further establishes this author\u2019s place in the hierarchy of southwestern writers of note.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1523667485i/39844835.jpg", "genres": ["Fiction", "Mystery"], "asin": "B07C64VK3L", "publisher": "RACLLC", "series": ["Navajo Nation Mystery"], "author": ["R. Allen Chappell"], "publishDate": 1523516400000, "ratingHistogram": [7, 23, 138, 422, 640], "ratingsCount": 1230, "reviewsCount": 41, "numPages": 309, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/26521489-a-most-extraordinary-pursuit", "title": "A Most Extraordinary Pursuit", "titleComplete": "A Most Extraordinary Pursuit (Emmaline Truelove, #1)", "description": "Known for \u201ccharming, original characters, a large dose of humor, and a plot that\u2019s fantastic fun,\u201d(New York Times beststelling author Jennifer Ashley) Juliana Gray presents an extraordinary novel of an uncommon pursuit... As the personal secretary of the recently departed Duke of Olympia\u2014and a woman of good character\u2014Miss Emmeline Rose Truelove never expected to be steaming through the Mediterranean on a luxuriously appointed yacht under the watchful and jovial eye of one Lord Silverton. But here they are, as improper as it is, on a quest to find the duke\u2019s heir, whereabouts unknown. An expert on anachronisms, the adventurous Maximilian Haywood was last seen at an archaeological dig on the island of Crete. And when Truelove and Silverton disembark, they are met with incidents of a violent nature: a ransacked flat, a murdered government employee, an assassination attempt. And as they steam from port to port on Max\u2019s trail, dodging danger at every turn, Truelove will discover the folly of her misconceptions\u2014about the whims of the heart, the desires of men, and the nature of time itself...", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1464041616i/26521489.jpg", "genres": ["Historical Mystery", "Time Travel", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Historical", "Paranormal", "Historical Romance", "Historical Fiction", "Romance", "Fantasy"], "asin": "0425277070", "isbn": "0425277070", "isbn13": "9780425277072", "publisher": "Berkley", "series": ["Emmeline Truelove"], "author": ["Juliana  Gray"], "publishDate": 1475564400000, "places": ["Crete"], "ratingHistogram": [41, 123, 458, 597, 249], "ratingsCount": 1468, "reviewsCount": 250, "numPages": 430, "language": "English"}
