{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/86714786-the-body-in-the-back-garden", "title": "The Body in the Back Garden", "titleComplete": "The Body in the Back Garden", "description": "In this queer cozy series debut, Luke Tremblay is about to discover that Crescent Cove has more than its fair share of secrets\u2026and some might be deadlier than others.Crescent Cove, a small hamlet on Vancouver Island, is the last place out-of-work investigative journalist Luke Tremblay ever wanted to see again. He used to spend summers here, until his family learned that he was gay and rejected him. Now, following his aunt\u2019s sudden death, he\u2019s inherited her entire estate, including her seaside cottage and the antiques shop she ran for forty years in Crescent Cove. Luke plans to sell everything and head back to Toronto as soon as he can\u2026but Crescent Cove isn\u2019t done with him just yet.When a stranger starts making wild claims about Luke\u2019s aunt, Luke sends him packing. The next morning, though, Luke discovers that the stranger has returned, and now he\u2019s lying dead in the back garden. To make matters worse, the officer leading the investigation is a handsome Mountie with a chip on his shoulder who seems convinced that Luke is the culprit. If he wants to prove his innocence and leave this town once and for all, Luke will have to use all his skills as a journalist to investigate the colorful locals while coming to terms with his own painful past.There are secrets buried in Crescent Cove, and the more Luke digs, the more he fears they might change the town forever.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1674740757i/86714786.jpg", "genres": ["Romance", "Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "M M Romance", "Mystery Thriller", "Adult", "Queer", "LGBT", "Contemporary"], "asin": "B0BN582M9W", "isbn": "1639104410", "publisher": "Crooked Lane Books", "series": ["Crescent Cove Mystery"], "author": ["Mark