{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/54578678-trouble-down-mexico-way", "title": "Trouble Down Mexico Way", "titleComplete": "Trouble Down Mexico Way (Blanche Murninghan Mystery, #2)", "description": "When Blanche \u201cBang\u201d Murninghan visits an exhibit of ancient Mayan ruins in Mexico City, she sees that all is not ancient. One of the mummies has a pink hair clip embedded in its hay-like do, and the texture of the skin is not quite right. Blanche, a part-time journalist, starts to dig for some answers and gets tangled in the mystery of the mummy at the Palacio Nacional. Her cousin and traveling companion, Haasi Hakla, aids and abets\u2014and puts the reins on Blanche. All the while, the two eat and drink their way across the city, following one hunch after another with a cast of colorful characters that include a prescient elderly chilanga , an amiable overworked detective, and a stunning doctor of shady deeds. The cousins are willing to risk kidnapping and attempted murder to get at the truth\u2014but first, Blanche stops for another excellent beer and Haasi delights in one more taco al pastor .", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1624721169i/54578678.jpg", "asin": "1611533759", "isbn": "1611533759", "isbn13": "9781611533750", "publisher": "Light Messages Publishing", "series": ["A Blanche Murninghan Mystery"], "author": ["Nancy Nau Sullivan"], "publishDate": 1624950000000, "ratingHistogram": [0, 1, 2, 5, 6], "ratingsCount": 14, "reviewsCount": 10, "numPages": 268, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/61106998-silenced-in-salem", "title": "Silenced in Salem", "titleComplete": "Silenced in Salem (Nina Brown Mysteries, #2)", "description": "Salem: A magical weekend escape offering a luxurious hotel, a psychic black cat, and a handsome \u201cbad boy\u201d chef who might just win the young foodie\u2019s heart.But when murder is on the menu, will she be the next victim?22-year-old Nina agrees to review a new boutique hotel for her lifestyle magazine. Shortly upon arrival, her mouth waters at the sight of the hotel\u2019s scrumptious chef.As the sugar plum culinarian shows the superstitious scribe the \u201csecret Salem\u201d of haunted burial grounds and witches\u2019 dens, mystery rustles through the crisp fall breeze.At the stroke of midnight, a s\u00e9ance invokes the spirit of the hotel\u2019s original owner. As the ghost swears revenge on his killer, guests laugh it off as Halloween fun.But when the present-day hotel owner gets whacked, police blame Nina\u2019s toque-topped lover.Can the enchanting chef be the culprit?Will Nina prove her creamy cuisiner\u2019s innocence and discover the real culprit before it\u2019s too late?Silenced in Salem is a fast-paced, laugh-out-loud funny cozy mystery, packed with quirky characters, mouth-watering cuisine, and an adorable, clairvoyant black kitten.You'll devour this delectable, cozy romantic mystery. Because in the black velvet Salem sky, love magic blazes bright.Get it Now", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1652737697i/61106998.jpg", "genres": ["Mystery"], "asin": "B09XLS76R4", "publisher": "SG Productions", "series": ["Nina Brown Mysteries"], "author": ["Cat Green"], "publishDate": 1661929200000, "ratingHistogram": [0, 2, 6, 32, 41], "ratingsCount": 81, "reviewsCount": 61, "numPages": 214, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/55375762-the-camel-trail", "title": "The Camel Trail", "titleComplete": "The Camel Trail", "description": "The story of a family on the edge, and another not far behind... Sarah Catchpole was raped and beaten by her husband one too many times. When Frankie is sent to prison, Sarah and her young son, Kevin, flee London and start over in the sleepy town of Padstow, Cornwall. They meet their new neighbours and their son, Martin, who is slowly dying from muscular dystrophy. He's almost wheelchair-bound but ever hopeful of being able to walk unaided the full length of The Camel Trail, an eleven-mile stretch of scenic path near the coast.But when Frankie is released from prison and tracks them down, the hunt begins. With Kevin and Martin missing, Sarah and Martin\u2019s parents are plunged headlong into a fight for their boys\u2019 survival and, ultimately, for their own redemption.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1600512213i/55375762.jpg", "genres": ["Fiction"], "asin": "B0053ZH1JA", "author": ["Peter J. Merrigan"], "publishDate": 1598943600000, "ratingHistogram": [3, 4, 17, 21, 44], "ratingsCount": 89, "reviewsCount": 17, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/15808868-final-sentence", "title": "Final Sentence", "titleComplete": "Final Sentence (Cookbook Nook Mystery, #1)", "description": "In need of a change, Jenna Hart leaves the high-pressure world of advertising to help her aunt, Vera, open a culinary bookshop and caf\u00e9. Back with her family in Crystal Cove, California, Jenna seems to have all the right ingredients for a fresh start\u2014until someone adds a dash of murder. As a marketing expert, Jenna wants to make sure the grand opening of the Cookbook Nook draws a crowd, and no one is better at getting attention than her old college roommate, celebrity chef Desiree Divine. But when Desiree arrives in quiet Crystal Cove to do a cookbook signing, the diva stirs up more trouble than business\u2026especially when she turns up dead. Known for stealing husbands and burning bridges, Desiree left behind plenty of suspects\u2014including Jenna. Though the celebrity\u2019s life always appeared to be an open book, Jenna will have to read between the lines in order to clear her name, and catch a killer before another body is served cold.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1413812117i/15808868.jpg", "genres": ["Books About Books", "Food", "Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Culinary", "Mystery Thriller", "Cooking", "Adult", "Cats"], "asin": "0425258041", "isbn": "0425258041", "isbn13": "9780425258040", "publisher": "Berkley", "series": ["Cookbook Nook Mystery"], "author": ["Daryl Wood Gerber"], "publishDate": 1372748400000, "characters": ["Jenna Hart", "Desiree Divine"], "places": ["Crystal Cove, California"], "ratingHistogram": [53, 119, 419, 545, 429], "ratingsCount": 1565, "reviewsCount": 287, "numPages": 283, "language": "English"}
