{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/29475503-the-girl-with-the-emerald-brooch", "title": "The Girl with the Emerald Brooch: Growing up: 1954 - 1965", "titleComplete": "The Girl with the Emerald Brooch: Growing up: 1954 - 1965", "description": "The true story of a working-class girl growing up in Northern England during the 1950s. One winter\u2019s day, Jacqueline\u2019s mother gives her an emerald brooch and tells her a secret. In the industrial city of Sheffield, ten year-old Jacqueline has to care for her whole her ailing mother, aged father, five year old sister and three-week old brother. At a tender age, when Jacqueline should be playing with her friends, she has to come to terms with birth and death, as well as cooking, cleaning and keeping the home fires burning. Jacqueline becomes a rebellious teenager, discovering boys, cigarettes and rock \u2018n\u2019 roll, before facing the challenges of growing up and choosing her own path in life. This wonderful tale is based on the writer\u2019s own childhood. You\u2019ll be gripped from the first sentence as you meet Jacqueline\u2019s family and friends. If you enjoy reading Catherine Cookson novels and watching Call the Midwife, you\u2019ll love this story.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1457599830i/29475503.jpg", "asin": "B01CRIXFZ4", "author": ["Jacqueline  Creek"], "publishDate": 1457424000000, "ratingHistogram": [1, 0, 2, 11, 18], "ratingsCount": 32, "reviewsCount": 5, "numPages": 312, "language": "English"}
