{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/35611346-the-curse-of-arundel-hall", "title": "The Curse of Arundel Hall", "titleComplete": "The Curse of Arundel Hall (The Yellow Cottage Vintage Mysteries #2)", "description": "This is an alternate cover edition for B01N36BX71 BRITAIN 1930's. ONE GHOST, ONE MURDER, ONE HUNDRED YEARS APART. BUT ARE THEY CONNECTED?Ella has discovered a secret room in The Yellow Cottage, but with it comes a ghost. Who was she? And how did she die? Ella needs to find the answers before either of them can find peace. But suddenly things take a nasty turn for the worse.Ella Bridges has been living on Linhay Island for several months but still hasn\u2019t discovered the identity of her ghostly guest. Deciding to research the history of her cottage for clues she finds it is connected to Arundel Hall, the large Manor House on the bluff, and when an invitation to dinner arrives realises it is the perfect opportunity to discover more.However the evening takes a shocking turn when one of their party is murdered. Is The Curse of Arundel Hall once again rearing its ugly head or is there a simpler explanation?Ella suddenly finds herself involved in two mysteries at once, and again joins forces with Scotland Yard\u2019s Police Commissioner to try and catch a killer. But will they succeed?A unique slant on the traditional whodunit and the humour peppered throughout are what makes these books firm favourites with readers.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1499345388i/35611346.jpg", "genres": ["Audiobook", "Murder Mystery", "Cozy Mystery", "British Literature", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Historical", "Paranormal", "Historical Fiction", "Crime"], "publisher": "Phantom Press", "series": ["Yellow Cottage Vintage Mysteries"], "author": ["J. New"], "publishDate": 1498892400000, "characters": ["Sergeant Baxter", "Phantom (Yellow Cottage Mysteries)", "Isobella \"Ella\" Bridges", "Aunt Margaret (Yello