{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/32273880-stone-cold-christmas", "title": "Stone Cold Christmas", "titleComplete": "Stone Cold Christmas", "description": "With Christmas only days away, Pelican Falls, a tiny hamlet not far from Lake Wogegon, is festooned with decorations and teeming with excitement. When Pastor Kathy Johnson rescues a runaway teenage girl, she could not have imagined waking the following morning to discover a body sprawled like a snow angel near the rear door at Grace Lutheran Church. As the blizzard passes and word of the fallen soul rages through the gossip mills at the Pelican Inn and the Curl Up &amp; Dye, some townsfolk come to suspect Pastor Kathy may have bonked the poor fellow over the head. The local police investigation sputters to get started amid old grudges so Pastor Kathy sets about to solve the case. The runaway girl may hold the key but she has vanished. The mystery deepens when the trail leads Pastor Kathy and her friends to be held captive in a pig barn. Will Pastor Kathy be rescued or in jail by Christmas?", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1475181709i/32273880.jpg", "asin": "1457549999", "isbn": "1457549999", "isbn13": "9781457549991", "publisher": "Dog Ear Publishing", "author": ["Larry Bergsgaard"], "publishDate": 1473750000000, "ratingHistogram": [0, 2, 4, 4, 1], "ratingsCount": 11, "reviewsCount": 9, "numPages": 256}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/30631259-mountain-mystery", "title": "Mountain Mystery", "titleComplete": "Mountain Mystery (Silver River Mystery, #1)", "description": "Welcome to the town of Silver River, hidden deep within the majestic Rocky Mountains. This historical, three-part series follows the lives of the Bradford-Bevan family, who live with their Aunt in a sprawling, three-story house. Abby, her sister, Rosemary, and their friend, Greta, will each face certain calamity, uncovering mysteries to maintain the peaceful existence of their town.After several miners fall ill, Doctor Roger Cameron finds himself volunteering to help in Silver River, a bustling mining town deep in the Colorado Mountains. What he hadn't counted on was Nurse Abigail Bradford-Bevan, who, despite wearing hideous-looking glasses, intrigues him.Following the death of her employer, Abigail stumbles upon his replacement at the post office, meeting a doctor on holiday from Philadelphia. Doctor Cameron must discover the source of the toxin, enlisting Abigail's help, although they unknowingly place themselves in danger. As the situation grows dire, Abby and Roger work together to solve the puzzle, the truth revealed after a shocking accident.Bonus Book Included: \"Prairie Madness\"", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1466070381i/30631259.jpg", "genres": ["Historical Mystery", "Historical Romance"], "asin": "B01H4REBSS", "publisher": "Love Lust Story", "series": ["Silver River Mystery"], "author": ["Carr\u00e9 White"], "publishDate": 1465974000000, "ratingHistogram": [1, 2, 5, 6, 9], "ratingsCount": 23, "reviewsCount": 3, "numPages": 309, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/21770750-till-tomorrow", "title": "Till Tomorrow", "titleComplete": "Till Tomorrow", "description": "David Mugisha, a popular athlete, faces ruin after an accident leaves him crippled for life. With the help of his foster sister, he battles with the demons of his past. Having surrounded himself with superficial friends and put his entire future plans in athletics, he is left alone and without money.He is soon employed as a journalist by a prominent newspaper to cover a nationwide competition and with the help of his ex-coach, Christopher, he uncovers a corruption scandal involving three wealthy and well respected men. One of those men is partly responsible for his irreversible spinal injury.He spends a massive amount of his time looking at the world through an overly critical eye and stubbornly refuses to come out of his pit of gloom. He constantly tries to reconnect with his past to see if he can come to terms with his tragedy. His attempt to expose the corruption scandal gives him the feeling that his life may not have ended in total ruin.After he fails to bring the culprits to justice he is tempted to slip back into his depression. A few unlikely people help him finally grasp the meaning of moving on.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1403471954i/21770750.jpg", "asin": "1622491416", "isbn": "1622491416", "isbn13": "9781622491414", "publisher": "Biblio Publishing/The Educational Publisher, Inc.", "author": ["Patrick Manzai"], "publishDate": 1357027200000, "ratingHistogram": [1, 2, 3, 7, 19], "ratingsCount": 32, "reviewsCount": 2, "numPages": 163, "language": "English"}
