{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/207455.Goose_in_the_Pond", "title": "Goose in the Pond", "titleComplete": "Goose in the Pond (Benni Harper, #4)", "description": "Benni Harper\u2014spirited ex-cowgirl, quilter, and folk art expert\u2014finds herself on the trail of a storybook killer in this mystery from Agatha Award-nominee Earlene Fowler.Hoping to relax after solving a murder in Wichita, Kansas, Beni and her new husband Gabe Ortiz are back in San Celina, California. But while Benni is jogging in the park, she happens upon the dead body of a library storyteller. It's an odd and disturbing scene\u2014the woman is still dressed in her Mother Goose costume, lying facedown in the lake.Benni's investigation takes her inside the Storyteller's Guild, where she finds out that Mother Goose was telling more than fairy tales. She was capable of airing the kind of secrets that destroy lives\u2014and inspire revenge...", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327138322i/207455.jpg", "genres": ["Detective", "Adult Fiction", "Cozy Mystery", "Quilting", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Mystery Thriller", "Adult", "Romance", "Contemporary"], "asin": "0425162397", "isbn": "0425162397", "isbn13": "9780425162392", "publisher": "Berkley Prime Crime", "series": ["Benni Harper"], "author": ["Earlene Fowler"], "publishDate": 883641600000, "characters": ["Benni Harper", "Gabriel Ortiz"], "places": ["San Celina, California"], "ratingHistogram": [10, 43, 535, 911, 650], "ratingsCount": 2149, "reviewsCount": 87, "numPages": 305, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Agatha Award", "awardedAt": 852105600000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/19807423-murder-at-cold-creek-college", "title": "Murder at Cold Creek College", "titleComplete": "Murder at Cold Creek College (Cold Creek Mysteries)", "description": "A dead colleague isn't the best way to start a semester or a romance.Although Sheridan Hendley is not a sleuth, when her colleague is murdered she assists the detective on the case as gets to know the campus. Her curiosity kicks in and she begins to draws connections among the people in Adam\u2019s life. She soon realizes many women have a strong motive for murder, and possibly a husband or two. As information leaks out on Adam\u2019s exploits to college administration, she\u2019s charged with creating sexual harassment training for faculty and students.Slashed tires are the first indication that asking too many questions and being seen with the detective make some people nervous. It becomes clear the murderer is afraid of what she might have found. In the meantime, as she works closely with the handsome detective, she hopes for romance in her future.Meet Sheridan Hendley and her friends in this first in a series of five cozy mysteries.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1387712470i/19807423.jpg", "genres": ["Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Adult", "Romance", "Contemporary"], "asin": "1492323829", "isbn": "1492323829", "isbn13": "9781492323822", "publisher": "CreateSpace Independent Publishing Platform", "series": ["Cold Creek"], "author": ["Christa Nardi"], "publishDate": 1381302000000, "ratingHistogram": [6, 19, 50, 107, 110], "ratingsCount": 292, "reviewsCount": 96, "numPages": 283, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17054.Stardust_of_Yesterday", "title": "Stardust of Yesterday", "titleComplete": "Stardust of Yesterday (de Piaget, #9; de Paiget/MacLeod, #1)", "description": "Dreaming of her wonderful castle, she imagined that it contained a handsome, brave knight\u2014Suddenly, her eyes flew open. She scrambled over her chair, looking with alarm at what was quivering in front of her, only an inch away from where her toes had dangled off the edge\u2026It was a sword.\u201cI\u2019ll not miss my mark a second time.\u201d A deep voice grated from behind her.She whirled around.It was her knight.It was also her ghost.Genevieve Buchanan inherited a castle\u2014and a ghost to go along with it. But Kendrick de Piaget was no typical ghost. He was a handsome and infuriatingly arrogant thirteenth-century knight. At first he wanted to frighten Genevieve, though she was more charmed than scared by his ghostly tricks. But when his thoughts turned to wooing her instead, Genevieve had to face her greatest fear: falling in love.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388365775i/17054.jpg", "genres": ["Time Travel", "Fiction", "Paranormal", "Historical", "Time Travel Romance", "Historical Romance", "Ghosts", "Romance", "Fantasy", "Paranormal Romance"], "asin": "042518238X", "isbn": "042518238X", "isbn13": "9780425182383", "publisher": "Berkley Publishing", "series": ["de Piaget", "de Piaget/MacLeod Romances: Publication Order"], "author": ["Lynn Kurland"], "publishDate": 986112000000, "characters": ["Kendrick de Paiget", "Genevieve Buchanan"], "places": ["England"], "ratingHistogram": [127, 195, 708, 1268, 1862], "ratingsCount": 4160, "reviewsCount": 213, "numPages": 368, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "RITA Award by Romance Writers of America", "awardedAt": 852105600000, "category": "Best Paranormal Romance & Best First Book", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18684152-schatten-ber-allerby", "title": "Schatten \u00fcber Allerby", "titleComplete": "Schatten \u00fcber Allerby", "description": "Die junge und attraktive Lady Michelle Carter-Jones ist tot, angeblich ist es Selbstmord \u2013 und das, obwohl sie wenige Tage zuvor zusam-men mit Mabel Clarence eine gro\u00dfe Geburtstagsparty f\u00fcr ihren \u00e4lteren, an den Rollstuhl gefesselten Ehemann geplant hat. F\u00fcr Mabel steht fest: Allen scheinbaren Beweisen zum Trotz \u2013 da kann etwas nicht stimmen!Als Pflegerin f\u00fcr Lord Carter-Jones getarnt, schleicht sie sich auf dem Herrensitz Allerby House ein und kommt einem schrecklichen Familiengeheimnis auf die Spur, das sie selbst in gr\u00f6\u00dfte Gefahr bringt.Nach \u201eDie Tote von Higher Barton\u201c und \u201eDer Tod schreibt mit\u201c ein neuer Fall f\u00fcr Mabel Clarence.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1381999411i/18684152.jpg", "asin": "B00FF8EO54", "isbn": "3940258245", "isbn13": "9783940258243", "publisher": "Goldfinch Verlag", "series": ["Cornwall-Krimi mit Mabel Clarence"], "author": ["Rebecca Mich\u00e9le"], "publishDate": 1379401200000, "characters": ["Mabel Clarence"], "ratingHistogram": [0, 2, 4, 11, 13], "ratingsCount": 30, "reviewsCount": 5, "numPages": 328, "language": "German"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/15753924-fit-to-be-dead", "title": "Fit to be Dead", "titleComplete": "Fit to be Dead (Aggie Mundeen Mystery, #1)", "description": "Lefty Award Finalist for Best Humorous Mystery.Chanticleer Award Winner (Mystery&amp;Mayhem category)WRY HUMOR AND A CLEVERLY WOVEN MYSTERYAggie Mundeen, single and pushing forty, fears nothing but middle age. When she moves from Chicago to San Antonio, she decides she better shape up before anybody discovers she writes the column, \u201cStay Young with Aggie.\u201d She takes Aspects of Aging at the University of the Holy Trinity and plunges into exercise at Fit and Firm. Rusty at flirting and mechanically inept, she irritates a slew of male exercisers, then stumbles into murder. She\u2019d like to impress the attractive detective with her sleuthing skills. But when the killer comes after her, the health club evacuates semi-clad patrons, and the detective has to stall his investigation to save Aggie\u2019s derriere.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1343751897i/15753924.jpg", "genres": ["Amateur Sleuth", "Cozy Mystery", "Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery Thriller", "Humor"], "publisher": "Southwest Publications", "series": ["Aggie Mundeen Mystery"], "author": ["Nancy G. West"], "publishDate": 1331794800000, "ratingHistogram": [12, 35, 66, 45, 34], "ratingsCount": 192, "reviewsCount": 45, "numPages": 336, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Lefty Award", "awardedAt": 1357027200000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18131018-the-great-scarecrow-invasion", "title": "The Great Scarecrow Invasion", "titleComplete": "The Great Scarecrow Invasion (The Reboot Files #5)", "description": "An alternate cover edition can be found here.When their latest assignment is debunked before Irene\u2019s Eerie Adventures can even get started Irene Waters and Troy Stenson take the opportunity to help out an old friend.Bob Cullens has been sidetracked from retirement to design an elaborate corn maze, but the job has been complicated because Bob\u2019s employer, farmer Evan Franklin, has trouble. Scarecrow trouble.So what could be the trouble with scarecrows in a fancy cornfield? Well, they\u2019re getting up and walking around and making a general nuisance of themselves.This could have dire consequences for the Franklin family. Seems a century or so ago a Franklin cast a spell to bring a scarecrow to life to run off their hated neighbors the Sullvans. Of course, as with all ill thought out deals with the supernatural, there were consequences, like coming back to take the souls of your ancestors in payment consequences. Needless to say the Franklins are a bit on edge to have animated scarecrows running about the place.So who\u2019s responsible for the scarecrow invasion and what is the mystery behind their deep, dark plan?Fortunately for Irene and Troy this is just another day at the office.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1372207640i/18131018.jpg", "asin": "B00DLO8H8E", "series": ["The Reboot Files"], "author": ["C.L. Ragsdale"], "publishDate": 1372057200000, "ratingHistogram": [1, 0, 2, 11, 3], "ratingsCount": 17, "reviewsCount": 1, "numPages": 100, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/16129273-malicious-mischief", "title": "Malicious Mischief", "titleComplete": "Malicious Mischief (A Rylie Keyes Mystery #1)", "description": "Is it strange to have the unemployment office on speed dial? Not for twenty-four-year-old college dropout Rylie Keyes. Her current job at a small retirement home is worlds more important than all her past gigs, though: if she loses this one, she won\u2019t be able to stop the forced sale of her and her grandfather\u2019s home, a house that has been in the family for ages. But keeping her job means figuring out the truth about a senior citizen who was found murdered while in her care. Explain that one, Miss Keyes.The late Otto Weiner was thought to be a penniless Nazi concentration camp survivor with a silly grudge against Rylie. However, Otto was not a liked man by any means, and his enemies will stop at nothing to keep their part in his murder secret.Forced to dust off the PI training she has to keep hidden from her ex-detective grandfather, Rylie must align with a circus-bike-wheeling Samoan while juggling the attention of two very hot cops who each get her all hot and bothered for very different reasons. And as she trudges through this new realm of perseverance, she has no idea that along the way she just might win, or lose, a little piece of her heart.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1370001303i/16129273.jpg", "genres": ["Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Chick Lit", "Adult"], "publisher": "Entangled Select", "series": ["A Rylie Keyes Mystery"], "author": ["Marianne Harden"], "publishDate": 1382425200000, "places": ["Bellevue, Washington"], "ratingHistogram": [8, 10, 22, 25, 20], "ratingsCount": 85, "reviewsCount": 31, "numPages": 320, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17725878-house-of-parrots", "title": "House of Parrots", "titleComplete": "House of Parrots", "description": "House of Parrots is a murder mystery novel set in a small village in England. It tells of Gerald Brown, the parrot man, who attracts something very nasty, a madman attacking his house and leaving dead birds on the doorstep stabbed through the heart with a dagger. It is a well-knit village community rocked to its core by the goings on, not to mention illicit love affairs, gay scandal and finally murder.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1399225604i/17725878.jpg", "isbn13": "9781301535347", "publisher": "Smashwords", "author": ["Hilary West"], "publishDate": 1364713200000, "ratingHistogram": [0, 0, 0, 0, 1], "ratingsCount": 1, "reviewsCount": 1, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17853797-daytona-dead", "title": "Daytona Dead", "titleComplete": "Daytona Dead", "description": "The honeymoon of Laura and Gerry Fitz is off to a fast-paced yet deadly start when they arrive in Florida. There is a maniac behind the wheel who needs to win at all costs. When he wins, life is great but when he loses he is DRIVEN TO KILL! The first victim off the starting line is Laura's ex-husband Lou, and she is taking it personally. Mix in a creepy cop and some unexpected surprises and you have a race for your life. Who will win and who will wipe out?", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1367002572i/17853797.jpg", "asin": "1460211340", "isbn": "1460211340", "isbn13": "9781460211342", "publisher": " FriesenPress", "series": ["Laura and Gerry"], "author": ["Karen H. Vaughan"], "publishDate": 1366095600000, "ratingHistogram": [0, 0, 0, 4, 19], "ratingsCount": 23, "reviewsCount": 13, "numPages": 208, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6549258-murder-jaz-tel-aviv", "title": "Murder, Jaz, & Tel Aviv", "titleComplete": "Murder, Jaz, & Tel Aviv (A Jazmine Davidson Adventure, #1)", "description": "Ahhh\u2026Tel Aviv in the summer: hot sun, beautiful beaches and a popping nightlife! Just the answer to Jazmine Davidson\u2019s dead-end life as an English teacher in cold and foggy San Francisco.Cousin Sara, up on the kibbutz, is thrilled to hear that Jaz has finally decided to give Israel a chance and plans for her arrival. But since kibbutz living might entail living in tents and washing her own clothes, Jaz opts to try and find work in Tel Aviv. Before long she gets her first private student and is on the road to living the life. Or at least she thought she was. A dead student? The mob? A cute cop? The CIA? Or is it the Mossad? Jaz finds herself in an insane world being interrogated by the police and assaulted by strangers, all of who seem to think she knows something she doesn\u2019t, and all of it in a language she doesn\u2019t understand even when they speak English. Frantic calls from Cousin Sara, faxes from the psychic aunt in California, questionable men in questionable professions \u2026Will Jaz be able to put all the pieces together before she herself is taken apart?", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1328557340i/6549258.jpg", "genres": ["Fiction", "Mystery"], "asin": "1439222282", "publisher": "BookSurge Publishing", "series": ["A Jazmine Davidson Adventure"], "author": ["Kate McVaugh"], "publishDate": 1233561600000, "characters": ["Dossam", "Jaz", "Cousin Sara", "Doobie", "Zeev"], "ratingHistogram": [1, 2, 5, 8, 6], "ratingsCount": 22, "reviewsCount": 8, "numPages": 204, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17978243-dyed-and-gone", "title": "Dyed and Gone", "titleComplete": "Dyed and Gone (An Azalea March Mystery, #1)", "description": "Hairstylist Azalea March is looking forward to a wild weekend in Las Vegas with her friends. Oh, sure, they\u2019re supposed to be there on business, attending the biggest hair show on the west coast, but that doesn\u2019t mean they can\u2019t have a little fun. But fun quickly turns to drama. On the first morning of the show, Dhane, the biggest celeb of the hair-styling world, is found dead. As it urns out Azalea\u2019s friend, Vivian, not only knew Dhane, but the tale she weaves of how they met is faker than a showgirl\u2019s uh\u2026 assets. When Vivian confesses to the murder and is arrested, Azalea knows there\u2019s no way she could have done it and suspects Vivian may be trying to protect someone. But who?Azalea now has to convince Alex, the sexy detective from her past, to help her prove Vivian\u2019s innocence and comb through clues more twisted than a spiral perm. But the truth is stranger than anything found on the Las Vegas Strip, and proving Vivian\u2019s innocence turns out to be more difficult than transforming a brunette into a blonde.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1380963764i/17978243.jpg", "genres": ["Romance", "Cozy Mystery", "Mystery", "Fiction", "Contemporary Romance", "Contemporary"], "asin": "1622661230", "isbn": "1622661230", "isbn13": "9781622661237", "publisher": "Entangled: Select", "author": ["Beth Yarnall"], "publishDate": 1395730800000, "ratingHistogram": [3, 7, 16, 43, 22], "ratingsCount": 91, "reviewsCount": 43, "numPages": 400, "language": "English"}
