{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/30178957-a-quiet-life-in-the-country", "title": "A Quiet Life in the Country", "titleComplete": "A Quiet Life in the Country (Lady Hardcastle Mysteries, #1)", "description": "Revised edition: This edition of A Quiet Life In The Country includes editorial revisions.Lady Emily Hardcastle is an eccentric widow with a secret past. Florence Armstrong, her maid and confidante, is an expert in martial arts. The year is 1908 and they\u2019ve just moved from London to the country, hoping for a quiet life.But it is not long before Lady Hardcastle is forced out of her self-imposed retirement. There\u2019s a dead body in the woods, and the police are on the wrong scent. Lady Hardcastle makes some enquiries of her own, and it seems she knows a surprising amount about crime investigation\u2026As Lady Hardcastle and Flo delve deeper into rural rivalries and resentment, they uncover a web of intrigue that extends far beyond the village. With almost no one free from suspicion, they can be certain of only one fact: there is no such thing as a quiet life in the country.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1472244528i/30178957.jpg", "genres": ["Audiobook", "Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Historical", "Mystery Thriller", "Historical Fiction", "Historical Mystery", "Crime", "Adult"], "asin": "B01ER14CRY", "isbn": "1503993264", "publisher": "Thomas & Mercer", "series": ["Lady Hardcastle Mysteries"], "author": ["T.E. Kinsey"], "publishDate": 1475564400000, "characters": ["Constable Sam Hancock", "Inspector Oliver Sunderland", "Harry Featherstonehaugh", "Roland Richman", "Sylvia Montgomery", "Edna Gibson", "Sergeant Walter Dobson", "Fred Spratt", "Florence Armstrong", "James Seddon", "Bartholomew \"Barty\" Dunn", "Maude Denton", "Ivor \"Skins\" Maloney", "Mrs. Brown (Hardcastle)", "Ida Seddon", "Captain Roger Summers", "Bert the handsome chauffeur", "Jenkins (Hardcastle)", "C