{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/50532271-saving-tuna-street", "title": "Saving Tuna Street", "titleComplete": "Saving Tuna Street (Blanche Murninghan Mystery, #1)", "description": "Blanche \u201cBang\u201d Murninghan is a part-time journalist with writer\u2019s block and a penchant for walking the beach on her beloved Santa Maria Island. Gran left her a cabin on Tuna Street, and she\u2019s got her friends and family--her itinerant cousin, Jack, and Cap, a lovable old fisherman who coddles her like a grandfather, and her friend, Liza, a realtor who looks like she emerged from central casting. All is well. Until the land-grabbing goons arrive from Chicago. Blanche finds herself in a tailspin, flabbergasted that so many things can go so wrong, so fast. Her friend, Bob Blankenship, Liza\u2019s partner, is found murdered in the parking lot of the marina, and she suspects the slick, handsome land developer Sergi Langstrom and his company of chaos are behind it all. Blanche keeps digging. All the way to hell. The goons, it seems, are a front for a drug cartel.The harder Blanche pushes against the source of trouble, the more she is sucked into the vortex of greed, murder, drug runners, and kidnapping (hers). The appearance of the mysterious Haasi, a tiny Native American with glossy braids and dark eyes, complicates things, and it\u2019s a good thing. She appears and disappears but always ends up at Blanche\u2019s side. They all keep getting closer to the sources of the spurious land development and the murder and the drug running. Who can look away? It\u2019s like watching a hurricane, which, literally, comes straight for Tuna Street.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1581778086i/50532271.jpg", "genres": ["Cozy Mystery", "Mystery"], "asin": "1611533309", "isbn": "1611533309", "isbn13": "9781611533309", "publisher": "Light Messages Publishing", "series": ["A Blanche Murninghan Mystery"], "author"