{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/58651537-murder-at-the-heights", "title": "Murder at the Heights: A Faye-Lynn Johnson Mystery", "titleComplete": "Murder at the Heights: A Faye-Lynn Johnson Mystery", "description": "IS SHE THE PERFECT WIFE?A beautiful spring day in Frederick is shattered when the home of a family of six becomes a crime five of them dead, one\u2014the mother\u2014missing. Was she lucky to have escaped? Or is her absence evidence of something sinister?OR IS SHE THE PERFECT KILLER?Detective Faye-Lynn Johnson is on the case seeking justice and must make sense of the clues left behind. The young woman who, whether as victim or suspect, is silently pleading, Look for me.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1627495569i/58651537.jpg", "asin": "B09B6JWDC4", "author": ["Ricky Corum"], "publishDate": 1627110000000, "ratingHistogram": [0, 0, 0, 3, 4], "ratingsCount": 7, "reviewsCount": 6, "numPages": 161, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/60019344-the-yarn-that-binds", "title": "The Yarn That Binds", "titleComplete": "The Yarn That Binds (Clear Creek Mysteries, #1)", "description": "Jemma hasn\u2019t been to the tiny Rocky Mountain town of Clear Creek in years, but when her grandmother tells her something strange is going on, Jemma drops everything to return and help untangle the clues. She arrives to flashing lights, a house full of police, and the news that her grandmother has been killed with her own yarn. After learning she inherits everything, Jemma is faced with the choice of casting on a new life by reopening her grandmother\u2019s yarn shop, or returning to her live-out-of-a-suitcase life as a travel vlogger.One thing\u2019s for sure \u2014 she\u2019s not leaving town until the mystery of her grandmother\u2019s death has unraveled. But when the deputy in charge of the investigation ignores clues Jemma stumbles upon, she decides to do her own poking around. Because her grandmother was right \u2014 there is something strange happening in Clear Creek.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1641226479i/60019344.jpg", "genres": ["Cozy Mystery", "Mystery"], "series": ["Clear Creek Mystery"], "author": ["Rebecca McKinnon"], "publishDate": 1649919600000, "ratingHistogram": [0, 0, 6, 11, 20], "ratingsCount": 37, "reviewsCount": 12, "numPages": 258, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/56268979-getaway-with-murder", "title": "Getaway With Murder", "titleComplete": "Getaway With Murder (Mountain Lodge Mystery, #1)", "description": "Getaway With Murder is the first in a cozy series from Diane Kelly set in a lodge in the Blue Ridge Mountains, where secrets hide behind every hill.As if hitting the half-century mark wasn\u2019t enough, Misty Murphy celebrated her landmark birthday by amicably ending her marriage and investing her settlement in a dilapidated mountain lodge at the top of the Blue Ridge Mountains. With the old inn teetering on both a bluff and bankruptcy, she must have lost her ever-loving mind.Luckily, handyman Rocky Crowder has a knack for rehabbing virtual ruins and for doing it on a dime, and to Misty\u2019s delight, the lodge is fully booked on opening night, every room filled with flexible folks who\u2019d slipped into spandex and ascended the peak for a yoga retreat with plans to namastay for a full week. Misty and her guests are feeling zen\u2014at least until the yoga instructor is found dead.With a killer on the loose and the lodge\u2019s reputation hanging in the balance, Misty must put her detective-skills to the test. Only one thing is as clear as a sunny mountain morning\u2014she must solve the crime before the lodge ends up, once again, on the brink.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1618287793i/56268979.jpg", "genres": ["Audiobook", "Southern", "Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Thriller", "Cats", "Mystery Thriller", "Animals", "Adult"], "asin": "1250815975", "isbn": "1250815975", "isbn13": "9781250815972", "publisher": "St. Martin's Paperbacks", "series": ["Mountain Lodge Mystery"], "author": ["Diane Kelly"], "publishDate": 1635231600000, "ratingHistogram": [10, 44, 261, 485, 274], "ratingsCount": 1074, "reviewsCount": 310, "numPages": 292, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/59482610-poisoned-in-provence", "title": "Poisoned in Provence", "titleComplete": "Poisoned in Provence (Nina Brown Mysteries, #1)", "description": "Provence: A magical start to bright new life\u2026\u2026garnished with buttery croissants, caf\u00e9 au lait, and a delectable French chef.But when murder is on the menu, will she be the next victim?Still reeling from a romantic betrayal, 22-year-old Nina travels to Provence, France to oversee her magazine\u2019s chef competition.Kitchen heat sends her swooning into the arms of a scrumptious French contestant Jacques, a tasty Cr\u00e8me Br\u00fbl\u00e9e of a chef she\u2019d love to nibble. As Jacques gives Nina a tour of his family\u2019s historic caves and magical gardens, secrets waft through the lilac-scented breeze.Secrets that come to light when the head judge shrieks \u201cpoison\u201d during the competition\u2019s climax.Can Jacques be the culprit?Will Nina prove her creamy cuisiner\u2019s innocence and discover the real culprit before it\u2019s too late?Poisoned in Provence is a fast-paced, laugh-out-loud funny cozy mystery, packed with quirky characters, mouth-watering cuisine, and the adorable fashionista French Bulldog, Jasper.You'll devour this delicious, cozy romance. Because in the warmth of French Country kitchens, love magic blazes bright.Get it now.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1635596240i/59482610.jpg", "genres": ["Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Paranormal", "Mystery Thriller", "Humor"], "asin": "B09KMGC6QJ", "publisher": "SG Publications", "series": ["Nina Brown Mysteries"], "author": ["Cat Green"], "publishDate": 1649919600000, "places": ["Provence"], "ratingHistogram": [12, 22, 88, 107, 126], "ratingsCount": 355, "reviewsCount": 67, "numPages": 180, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/55517140-lynch", "title": "Lynch", "titleComplete": "Lynch (Rider, #2)", "description": "THE SURVIVORS: Eighteen months after their ordeal in London, Kane Rider and Margaret Bernhard are secured in witness protection and moving on with their lives.But Alberto Ramirez isn't about to let them off so easily.THE ASSASSIN: Ex-Spanish soldier turned hired-hitman Miguel Fernandez has a taste for blood. Employed by kingpin Ramirez, he's now on the trail of a man and woman who disappeared a year and a half ago.THE LAW: Interpol detective Ann Clark, responsible for getting Kane and Margaret into witness protection, is at a loose end. Suspended from the force for a careless mistake, but determined to protect her charges, the decisions she makes now will have consequences for them all.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1601476254i/55517140.jpg", "genres": ["LGBT"], "asin": "1548165867", "isbn": "1548165867", "isbn13": "9781548165864", "publisher": "Createspace Independent Publishing Platform", "series": ["Rider"], "author": ["Peter J. Merrigan"], "publishDate": 1598943600000, "ratingHistogram": [0, 0, 4, 4, 8], "ratingsCount": 16, "reviewsCount": 2, "numPages": 296, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/35103761-class-reunions-are-murder", "title": "Class Reunions Are Murder", "titleComplete": "Class Reunions Are Murder (A Poppy McAllister Mystery, #1)", "description": "Newly widowed and stuck in a middle-aged funk, Poppy has been running on cookies, infomercials, and one-sided chats with her cat for months. There's no way on earth she's attending her twenty-five-year class reunion--especially after receiving a very bizarre letter from Barbie, the popular cheerleader who taunted her all through high school. At least, not until Poppy's best friend practically drags her to the event . . . Using the dreaded homecoming as an excuse to visit her eccentric Aunt Ginny, Poppy vows to leave Cape May with pride and Spanx intact. Too bad Barbie is still the queen of mean at the reunion. And worse, that her dead body is lying right in front of Poppy's old locker. Singled out as the killer, it's up to Poppy to confront her past and clear her name. But between protecting her aunt from disaster and tackling a gluten-free diet, can Poppy crack the case before she's voted Most Likely to Die by the murderer?", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1494340161i/35103761.jpg", "genres": ["Audiobook", "Amazon", "Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Mystery Thriller", "Humor", "Crime", "Adult", "Contemporary"], "asin": "1496713036", "isbn": "1496713036", "isbn13": "9781496713032", "publisher": "Kensington", "series": ["A Poppy McAllister Mystery"], "author": ["Libby Klein"], "publishDate": 1517299200000, "places": ["New Jersey"], "ratingHistogram": [30, 58, 281, 588, 613], "ratingsCount": 1570, "reviewsCount": 366, "numPages": 407, "language": "English"}
