{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/44345091-paw-of-the-jungle", "title": "Paw of the Jungle", "titleComplete": "Paw of the Jungle (Paw Enforcement #8)", "description": "Police officer Megan Luz and her K-9 partner in crime, Brigit, are on all fours as they try to solve their latest Lone Star mystery.AT THE ZOOThe weather is beautiful, work is slow, and her canine colleague could use a walk. What better day for Megan to take Brigit to the Fort Worth Zoo, where they can let loose and witness the law and order of nature unfold? But what begins as a fun field trip turns serious when a pair of rare hyacinth macaws named Fabiana and Fernando goes missing. Is the new custodian, a gentle soul who happens to be an ex-convict, to blame? Or is something far more sinister afoot?AND ON THE HUNTThe birds are worth thousands of dollars, and the list of people on the premises who might have stolen them is long. Soon other animals start disappearing. . .and Megan and Brigit have their hands and paws full of suspects. But when a rare black rhino is taken from the zoo, presumably for its black-market-friendly horn, time is of the essence. Can Megan and Brigit find out who\u2019s behind the mystery\u2014before they too become prey?", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1557107329i/44345091.jpg", "genres": ["Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Romance", "Animals"], "asin": "B07P9LPNHB", "publisher": "St. Martin's Paperbacks", "series": ["Paw Enforcement"], "author": ["Diane Kelly"], "publishDate": 1574755200000, "ratingHistogram": [1, 11, 64, 148, 182], "ratingsCount": 406, "reviewsCount": 110, "numPages": 365, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/53438968-murder-in-devil-s-cove", "title": "Murder in Devil's Cove", "titleComplete": "Murder in Devil's Cove (A Book Magic Novel, #1)", "description": "\u201c...a deftly crafted and impressively original novel by an author with a genuine flair for originality...certain to be an unusual, immediate and enduringly popular addition to community library Mystery/Suspense collections\u2026\u201d ~Midwest Book Review*Cradled in the waters between North Carolina\u2019s Outer Banks and the mainland is the island of Devil\u2019s Cove, the town where Pippin Lane Hawthorne was born. After the death of her mother\u2014and twenty years after being abandoned by her father\u2014Pippin and her twin brother, Grey, are back. Inheriting their parents\u2019 old beach house on Rum Runner\u2019s Lane is like a strong wind at their back, pushing them to safe ground. They are home at last.But what was supposed to be a chance at a new life turns sinister when her father\u2019s old fishing boat reveals a dark secret. As the truth about what really happened to Leo Hawthorne unspools, Pippin realizes that an ancient curse her parents fought to break has found her.Now Pippin must embrace her fate as a bibliomancer and learn how to \u2018read\u2019 the books she\u2019s always shied away from. Only then will she be able to discover the truth about what really happened to her parents and continue their efforts to break the curse that has haunted the Lane family for two thousand years.\u201cA magical blend of books, mystery, and smart sleuthing, Melissa Bourbon\u2019s Murder in Devil\u2019s Cove offers mystery readers everything they crave and stands out in the crowded cozy genre. This captivating new series will leave readers spellbound.\u201d-NYT and USA bestselling author, Ellery Adams", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1706831500i/53438968.jpg", "genres": ["Cozy Mystery", "Magic", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Paranormal", "Mystery Thriller", "Magical Realism", "Family", "Fantasy", "Contemporary"], "publisher": "Lake House Press", "series": ["Pippin Lane Hawthorne Mysteries"], "author": ["Melissa Bourbon"], "publishDate": 1600758000000, "characters": ["Pippin Lane Hawthorne, Cassandra (Cassie) Lane Hawthorne, Grey Hawthorne, Leo Hawthorne, Daisy Santiago, Ruby Malone, Jamie McAd"], "places": ["Devil's Cove, Outer Banks, North Carolina"], "ratingHistogram": [2, 6, 63, 113, 188], "ratingsCount": 372, "reviewsCount": 117, "numPages": 306, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/42112391-the-trouble-with-tigers", "title": "The Trouble with Tigers", "titleComplete": "The Trouble with Tigers (Shenanigans, #2)", "description": "Lions and tigers and skunks, oh my! Kandi Cain\u2019s a psychic pet detective. Her cases range from wrangling baby goats, to finding lost critters. Her current case is rescuing a lion from a Nigerian warlord. Kandi knew dressing up as a demonic clown and walking a lion down a city street would freak people out. But, wow! She didn\u2019t expect Armageddon.The hot as hell Detective Dutch Callaghan\u2019s on her trail again and showing more than a professional interest. Kandi\u2019s talents have attracted the attention of a CIA black ops agent who wants her to steal twelve endangered white tigers from a Pakistani warlord. The mission\u2019s crucial to prevent a terrorist attack.Wait! What? Terrorists? What had she gotten herself into? Kandi wasn\u2019t a superhero. She couldn\u2019t bend steel with her bare hands, and she wasn\u2019t faster than a speeding bullet. She\u2019s Doctor Doolittle. She talks to the animals and occasionally the dead.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1565816429i/42112391.jpg", "genres": ["Paranormal", "M F Romance", "Romance", "Humor", "Paranormal Romance", "Contemporary", "Police"], "publisher": "Smashwords", "series": ["Shenanigans"], "author": ["Gail Koger"], "publishDate": 1568617200000, "ratingHistogram": [2, 4, 19, 50, 139], "ratingsCount": 214, "reviewsCount": 36, "numPages": 184, "language": "English"}
