{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/25801128-mercy-mayhem", "title": "Mercy & Mayhem", "titleComplete": "Mercy & Mayhem (Mercy Mares Cozy Mystery #1)", "description": "Traveling nurse Mercy Mares needs three things in life: the unconditional love of her daughter, her best friend and mentor's constant wisdom, and a new engine for her twenty-year old car. A new job posting halfway across the country promises to satisfy one of those needs, but when her patient's spouse dies within minutes of meeting her, she will soon find out that she's going to need a lot more than car repairs. What was touted as the friendliest town in America soon turns on her and it will be up to her to connect the dots and find the true murderer, but doing so will be no easy feat. With memory impaired witnesses, a meddling medical staff, and a cast of characters dead set on keeping their community free of strangers, Mercy will need a little help from her loved ones and a lot of luck to get herself out of this jam or risk losing everything she's worked so hard to achieve. Find out what happens when mayhem becomes synonymous with Mercy in this humorous, slightly irreverent Cozy Medical Mystery novel!(This a previously-published edition of ASIN B010EJQT6K, which is located at: https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/4....)", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1435348609i/25801128.jpg", "genres": ["Amazon", "Cozy Mystery", "Mystery", "Fiction", "Medical", "Contemporary"], "publisher": "Ava Mallory", "series": ["Mercy Mares Cozy Mystery"], "author": ["Ava Mallory"], "publishDate": 1437116400000, "ratingHistogram": [16, 55, 147, 231, 244], "ratingsCount": 693, "reviewsCount": 77, "numPages": 215, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/55274708-howl-play", "title": "Howl Play", "titleComplete": "Howl Play (The Spellwood Witches #2)", "description": "A novice witch. A collie companion. Can this clever duo put noses to the ground to chase down a killer?Sarah Spellwood can\u2019t wait to learn all her powerful ancestor\u2019s magic and repair the reputation of witches. But despite hours of study and her talking dog\u2019s support, she still doubts her spellcasting skill. And she\u2019s about to face a major test when she\u2019s plunged into a battle between good and evil after the enchanted forest\u2019s protective deed is stolen and the town clerk brutally murdered\u2026With the finger pointing at woodland wolves for the fatal mauling, Sarah and her pooch pal vow to help the handsome police officer Eli Strongheart dig up the truth and clear the innocent creatures\u2019 names. But when darkness rises to threaten the unprotected woods and its inhabitants, she\u2019ll need to fight a formidable magical enemy to stop its destruction.Can Sarah save the wolves and recover the deed before Witchland meets a terrible fate?Howl Play is the second book in the sweet Spellwood Witches cozy mystery series. If you like cute flirty romance, discovering one\u2019s true destiny, and love for animals, then you\u2019ll adore Melanie Snow\u2019s barking-ly fun adventure.Buy Howl Play to let supernatural talent off the leash today!", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1599581206i/55274708.jpg", "genres": ["Witches", "Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Paranormal"], "asin": "B08H5WKTWB", "publisher": "Spirit Paw Press, LLC", "series": ["The Spellwood Witches"], "author": ["Melanie  Snow"], "publishDate": 1601967600000, "ratingHistogram": [1, 3, 14, 32, 94], "ratingsCount": 144, "reviewsCount": 49, "numPages": 156, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18167479-murder-at-the-breakers", "title": "Murder at the Breakers", "titleComplete": "Murder at the Breakers (Gilded Newport Mysteries #1)", "description": "For fans of HBO\u2019s The Gilded Age, explore the dark side of the alluring world of America\u2019s 19th century elite in this gripping series of riveting mysteries\u2026Newport, Rhode Island, August 1895: She may be a less well-heeled relation, but as second cousin to millionaire patriarch Cornelius Vanderbilt, twenty-one-year-old Emma Cross is on the guest list for a grand ball at the Breakers, the Vanderbilts\u2019 summer home. She also has a job to do\u2014report on the event for the society page of the Newport Observer.But Emma observes much more than glitz and gaiety when she witnesses a murder. The victim is Cornelius Vanderbilt\u2019s financial secretary, who plunges off a balcony faster than falling stock prices. Emma\u2019s black sheep brother Brady is found in Cornelius\u2019s bedroom passed out next to a bottle of bourbon and stolen plans for a new railroad line. Brady has barely come to before the police have arrested him for the murder. But Emma is sure someone is trying to railroad her brother and resolves to find the real killer at any cost\u2026", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1379896701i/18167479.jpg", "genres": ["Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Historical", "Mystery Thriller", "Suspense", "Historical Fiction", "Romance", "Historical Mystery", "Crime"], "asin": "0758290829", "isbn": "0758290829", "isbn13": "9780758290823", "publisher": "Kensington", "series": ["Gilded Newport Mysteries"], "author": ["Alyssa Maxwell"], "publishDate": 1395730800000, "places": ["Newport, Rhode Island"], "ratingHistogram": [79, 375, 1902, 2369, 1445], "ratingsCount": 6170, "reviewsCount": 659, "numPages": 282, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/33632753-single-malt-murder", "title": "Single Malt Murder", "titleComplete": "Single Malt Murder (Whisky Business Mystery, #1)", "description": "Abigail Logan never expected to inherit a whisky distillery in the Scottish Highlands. But in the first novel of an engaging new series blending fine spirits with chilling mystery, Abi finds that there are secrets lurking in the misty glens that some will go to any lengths to protect . . . even murder.When Abi inherits her uncle\u2019s quaint and storied single malt distillery, she finds herself immersed in a competitive high-stakes business that elicits deep passions and prejudices. An award-winning photojournalist, Abi has no trouble capturing the perfect shot\u2014but making the perfect shot is another matter. When she starts to receive disturbing, anonymous threats, it\u2019s clear that someone wants her out of the picture. But Abi\u2019s never been one to back down from a fight.Arriving on the scene with her whisky-loving best friend, Patrick, and an oversized wheaten terrier named Liam, Abi seems to put everyone in the bucolic village on edge\u2014especially her dour but disturbingly attractive head distiller. Acts of sabotage and increasingly personal threats against Abi make it clear that she is not welcome. When one of Abi\u2019s new employees is found floating facedown in a vat of whisky, Abi is determined to use her skills as an investigative journalist to identify the cold-blooded killer and dispense a dram of justice before he strikes again. But distilling truth from lies is tricky, especially when everyone seems to have something to hide.Melinda Mullet\u2019s delightful Whisky Business mysteries can be read together or separately. Enjoy SINGLE MALT MURDER | DEATH DISTILLED | DEADLY DRAM | DIED IN THE WOOL", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1483026723i/33632753.jpg", "genres": ["Audiobook", "Murder My