{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/706843.Dark_Tort", "title": "Dark Tort", "titleComplete": "Dark Tort (A Goldy Bear Culinary Mystery, #13)", "description": "The New York Times bestselling author of Double Shot cooks up a knockout treat featuring irrepressible caterer Goldy Schulz that gives new meaning to the phrase, \u201clet\u2019s kill all the lawyers\u201d I tripped over the body of Dusty Routt sometime after 10 on the evening of October 19th. Goldy Schulz has a lucrative new gig, preparing breakfasts and conference room snacks for a local law firm. It\u2019s time consuming, but Goldy is enjoying it\u2015until the night she arrives to find the firm\u2019s paralegal dead. The poor girl also happens to be Goldy\u2019s next-door neighbor, and now her grieving mother begs Goldy to find out who murdered her daughter. Just because the police are on the case doesn\u2019t mean Goldy can\u2019t do a little snooping\u2015and catering\u2015too. Before long, Goldy is knee-deep in suspects, one of whom is very dangerous and very liable to cook Goldy\u2019s goose.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388193988i/706843.jpg", "genres": ["Audiobook", "Food", "Adult Fiction", "Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Culinary", "Mystery Thriller", "Chick Lit", "Cooking"], "asin": "0060527323", "isbn": "0060527323", "isbn13": "9780060527327", "publisher": "William Morrow Paperbacks", "series": ["Goldy Bear Culinary Mystery"], "author": ["Diane Mott Davidson"], "publishDate": 1182841200000, "ratingHistogram": [58, 398, 2577, 3202, 2060], "ratingsCount": 8295, "reviewsCount": 466, "numPages": 449, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6855.Smitten", "title": "Smitten", "titleComplete": "Smitten (Elsie Hawkins, #2)", "description": "Single mom Lizabeth Kane isn't exactly carpenter material -- she's never picked up a hammer in her life. But she desperately needs the construction job that builder Matt Hallahan is offering. And even though he knows trouble is ahead, Matt can't refuse Lizbeth's irresistible smile.Matt Hallahan isn't exactly relationship material -- he has always been too busy working on other people's houses to make a home of his own. And even though she knows better, Lizabeth can't stop thinking about the rugged carpenter.Is the relationship Matt and Lizabeth are building solid -- or more like a house of cards?", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1406693496i/6855.jpg", "genres": ["Audiobook", "Romance", "Comedy", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Chick Lit", "Adult", "Contemporary Romance", "Humor", "Contemporary"], "asin": "0060598875", "isbn": "0060598875", "isbn13": "9780060598877", "publisher": "HarperTorch", "series": ["Elsie Hawkins"], "author": ["Janet Evanovich"], "publishDate": 1153810800000, "characters": ["Elsie Hawkins", "Lizabeth Kane", "Matt Hallahan"], "ratingHistogram": [232, 1278, 4648, 4083, 3836], "ratingsCount": 14077, "reviewsCount": 506, "numPages": 234, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/574782.The_Last_Suppers", "title": "The Last Suppers", "titleComplete": "The Last Suppers (A Goldy Bear Culinary Mystery, #4)", "description": "A lusciously lethal novel by the New York Times bestselling author of Sticks &amp; Scones\u201cThe main course on Davidson\u2019s latest menu, served with lively pacing and characterization, is satisfying and tasty.\u201d\u2014 Publishers WeeklyIt should be the happiest day of Goldy\u2019s life. The Colorado caterer is about to tie the knot with the man of her dreams, homicide detective Tom Schultz. But minutes before the ceremony is to begin, Tom phones with an urgent The wedding is off, and the reason is murder!\u00a0Tom was on his way to the church when he stopped to pick up Father Olson\u2014and found the rector shot and dying. Yet by the time Tom\u2019s fellow officers arrive at the crime scene, Tom has disappeared. Has the groom been abducted by the killer? Or has he gotten cold feet and walked out of Goldy\u2019s life?\u00a0For better or worse, Goldy needs to know the truth. So she puts her exquisitely decorated wedding cake on ice and begins to search for clues. Her fianc\u00e9\u2019s life\u2014and her future happiness\u2014will lead her to an unsavory killer whose unholy passion make Goldy a widow before she\u2019s a wife.Featuring original recipes for such heavenly delights as monster cinnamon rolls, savory shrimp on wheels, and sinful first wasp latkes!", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388193989i/574782.jpg", "genres": ["Audiobook", "Food", "Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Culinary", "Mystery", "Mystery Thriller", "Chick Lit", "Cooking", "Humor"], "asin": "055357258X", "isbn": "055357258X", "isbn13": "9780553572582", "publisher": "Bantam Books", "series": ["Goldy Bear Culinary Mystery"], "author": ["Diane Mott Davidson"], "publishDate": 809938800000, "ratingHistogram": [68, 408, 2861, 3836, 2626], "ratingsC