{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/376345.Double_Shot", "title": "Double Shot", "titleComplete": "Double Shot (A Goldy Bear Culinary Mystery, #12)", "description": "New York Times bestselling author Diane Mott Davidson has taken readers by storm with clever mysteries filled with tantalizing plots and mouthwatering recipes. In her twelfth novel -- her tastiest tale yet -- the ingenious storyteller whips up a rich souffl#233; of murder and mischief. The governor of Colorado has commuted the prison sentence of Goldy Schulz's ultra-handsome, ultra-charming, ultra-wealthy, ultra-venal ex-husband, Dr. John Richard Korman, otherwise known to Goldy as the Jerk. He's released, and soon afterward Goldy becomes the victim of threats, rumors, and violence.Then there's a murder and suspicion centers on Goldy. Suddenly, she is faced with the challenge of running her successful catering business while fending off two persistent detectives.Caught in a web of secrets and lies that could tear her family apart, Goldy must use all of her considerable powers of detection to find the real killer before she herself becomes a target.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1340227771i/376345.jpg", "genres": ["Audiobook", "Food", "Adult Fiction", "Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Culinary", "Mystery Thriller", "Chick Lit", "Cooking"], "asin": "0060527293", "isbn": "0060527293", "isbn13": "9780060527297", "publisher": "William Morrow", "series": ["Goldy Bear Culinary Mystery"], "author": ["Diane Mott Davidson"], "publishDate": 1098169200000, "ratingHistogram": [78, 413, 3123, 4588, 3915], "ratingsCount": 12117, "reviewsCount": 451, "numPages": 310, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/15810108-woof-at-the-door", "title": "Woof at the Door", "titleComplete": "Woof at the Door (Call of the Wilde #1)", "description": "Animal behaviorist Grace Wilde keeps her ability to psychically communicate with furry and feathered critters under wraps. But when a Doberman turns out to be the only witness to a crime, Grace will have to let the cat out of the bag in order to catch a killer. Grace Wilde\u2019s job is anything but normal. When she\u2019s not helping out at the zoo by comforting agitated lemurs, she\u2019s listening to the woes of annoyed house pets. Grace\u2019s life gets even more complicated, though, when the cops summon her to a crime scene to help deal with the murder victim\u2019s terrified Doberman. The pooch turns out to be the only one who saw what happened the night of the shooting\u2014and only Grace can get the information out of him. The problem is, how will Grace tell the distractingly gorgeous Sergeant Kai Duncan that it\u2019s the dog who\u2019s giving her the intel without spilling her big secret or sounding crazy? Left on her own, Grace will have to follow the pup\u2019s lead to track down the killer. But she\u2019ll have to be careful\u2014or curiosity may end up killing the cat whisperer.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1362955914i/15810108.jpg", "genres": ["Cozy Mystery", "Fantasy", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Paranormal", "Paranormal Mystery", "Dogs", "Mystery Thriller", "Romance", "Animals"], "asin": "0425257193", "isbn": "0425257193", "isbn13": "9780425257197", "publisher": "Berkley", "series": ["Call of the Wilde"], "author": ["Laura Morrigan"], "publishDate": 1372748400000, "ratingHistogram": [8, 28, 183, 509, 579], "ratingsCount": 1307, "reviewsCount": 201, "numPages": 305, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/4728979-silent-on-the-moor", "title": "Silent on the Moor", "titleComplete": "Silent on the Moor (Lady Julia Grey, #3)", "description": "In Grimsgrave Hall, enigmatic Nicholas Brisbane has inherited a ruined estate, replete with uncanny tenants and one unwanted houseguest: Lady Julia Grey. Despite his admonitions to stay away, Lady Julia arrives in Yorkshire to find Brisbane as remote and maddeningly attractive as ever. Cloistered together, they share the moldering house with the proud but impoverished remnants of an ancient family: the sort that keeps their bloodline pure and their secrets close. Lady Allenby and her daughters, dependent upon Brisbane and devastated by their fall in society, seem adrift on the moor winds, powerless to change their fortunes. But poison does not discriminate between classes.... A mystery unfolds from the rotten heart of Grimsgrave, one Lady Julia may have to solve alone, as Brisbane appears inextricably tangled in its heinous twists and turns. But blood will out, and before spring touches the craggy northern landscape, Lady Julia will have uncovered a Gypsy witch, a dark rider, and a long-buried legacy of malevolence and evil. Deanna Raybourn spins a gripping tale of loyalty and lust, set against the wild beauty of the Yorkshire moors.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1475894981i/4728979.jpg", "genres": ["British Literature", "Mystery", "Fiction", "Historical", "Victorian", "Mystery Thriller", "Historical Romance", "Historical Fiction", "Romance", "Historical Mystery"], "asin": "0778326144", "isbn": "0778326144", "isbn13": "9780778326144", "publisher": "Mira Books", "series": ["Lady Julia Grey"], "author": ["Deanna Raybourn"], "publishDate": 1235462400000, "characters": ["Valerius March", "Hilda Allenby", "Rosalie Smith", "Godwin Allenby", "Portia, Lady Bettiscombe", "Lady Julia Grey", "Lady Allenby", "Ailith Allenby", "Ni