{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6553733-the-mapping-of-love-and-death", "title": "The Mapping of Love and Death", "titleComplete": "The Mapping of Love and Death (Maisie Dobbs, #7)", "description": "The story opens in August 1914 in the Santa Ynez Valley in California. Michael Clifton\u2014youngest son of an Englishman who had emigrated to America when he was in his late teens, in search of his fortune\u2014has just purchased a tract of land he believes is rich with oil. Fate steps in when Michael learns Britain is going to war in Europe. In a moment of loyalty to his father\u2019s homeland, he decides to travel to England to enlist for service.In the spring of 1932, after Michael\u2019s remains are discovered in France, his wealthy parents hire Maisie Dobbs to find the woman\u2014identified only as \u201cThe English Nurse\u201d\u2014who wrote a series of love letters discovered among Michael\u2019s belongings.The investigation takes Maisie from London\u2019s most exclusive drawing rooms to its most downtrodden neighborhoods, forcing her to wrestle with memories of serving as a nurse in the Great War and of the passionate wartime romance that ended in tragedy. But as she delves into what she discovers to be a long-hidden crime, the investigator realizes unearthing buried secrets can lead to present-day danger.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1329659691i/6553733.jpg", "genres": ["Detective", "Audiobook", "British Literature", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Historical", "Mystery Thriller", "Historical Fiction", "Historical Mystery", "Crime"], "asin": "0061727660", "isbn": "0061727660", "isbn13": "9780061727665", "publisher": "Harper", "series": ["Maisie Dobbs"], "author": ["Jacqueline Winspear"], "publishDate": 1269327600000, "characters": ["Maisie Dobbs"], "places": ["London, England"], "ratingHistogram": [131, 365, 3650, 12995, 11647], "ratingsCount": 28788, "reviewsCount": 2159, "numPages": 3