{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/11509014-buried-in-a-book", "title": "Buried in a Book", "titleComplete": "Buried in a Book (Novel Idea, #1)", "description": "After losing her job as a journalist at the age of forty-five, Lila Wilkins accepts an internship at A Novel Idea, a thriving literary agency in North Carolina. Being paid to read seems perfect to Lila, although it's difficult with the cast of quirky co-workers and piles of query letters. But when a penniless aspiring author drops dead in the agency's waiting room-and Lila discovers a series of threatening letters-she's determined to find out who wrote him off.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1317586180i/11509014.jpg", "genres": ["Books About Books", "Adult Fiction", "Cozy Mystery", "The United States Of America", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Mystery Thriller", "Romance", "Adult", "Contemporary"], "asin": "0425246191", "isbn": "0425246191", "isbn13": "9780425246191", "publisher": "Berkley Publishing Group", "series": ["Novel Idea"], "author": ["Lucy Arlington"], "publishDate": 1328601600000, "characters": ["Lila Wilkins"], "places": ["Inspiration Valley, North Carolina"], "ratingHistogram": [56, 193, 848, 1107, 736], "ratingsCount": 2940, "reviewsCount": 441, "numPages": 285, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7091488-dead-in-the-family", "title": "Dead in the Family", "titleComplete": "Dead in the Family (Sookie Stackhouse, #10)", "description": "It's all about family ...Sookie Stackhouse is dealing with a whole host of family problems, ranging from her own kin (a non-human fairy and a telepathic second cousin) demanding a place in her life, to her lover Eric's vampire sire, an ancient being who arrives with Eric's 'brother' in tow at a most inopportune moment. And Sookie's tracking down a distant relation of her ailing neighbour (and ex), Vampire Bill Compton.In addition to the multitude of family issues complicating her life, the werewolf pack of Shreveport has asked Sookie for a special favour, and since Sookie is an obliging young woman, she agrees. But this favour for the wolves has dire results for Sookie, who is still recovering from the trauma of her abduction during the Fairy War.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1290479828i/7091488.jpg", "genres": ["Vampires", "Urban Fantasy", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Paranormal", "Werewolves", "Romance", "Supernatural", "Fantasy", "Paranormal Romance"], "asin": "B00F1XVLOA", "isbn": "0441018645", "isbn13": "9780441018642", "publisher": "Ace Books", "series": ["Sookie Stackhouse"], "author": ["Charlaine Harris"], "publishDate": 1262332800000, "characters": ["Sam Merlotte", "Jason Stackhouse", "Bill Compton", "Alcide Herveaux", "Pam Ravenscroft", "Sookie Stackhouse", "Tara Thornton", "Eric Northman"], "places": ["Bon Temps, Louisiana"], "ratingHistogram": [2056, 9641, 42763, 57435, 51861], "ratingsCount": 163756, "reviewsCount": 5782, "numPages": 320, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Goodreads Choice Award", "awardedAt": 1262332800000, "category": "Paranormal Fantasy and Nominee for Favorite Book", "hasWon": null}]}
