{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/905887.Them_Bones", "title": "Them Bones", "titleComplete": "Them Bones (Sarah Booth Delaney, #1)", "description": "No self-respecting lady would allow herself to end up in Sarah Booth's situation. Unwed, unemployed, and over thirty, she's flat broke and about to lose the family plantation. Not to mention being haunted by the ghost of her great-great-grandmother's nanny, who never misses an opportunity to remind her of her sorry state--or to suggest a plan of action, like ransoming her friend's prize pooch to raise some cash.But soon Sarah Booth's walk on the criminal side leads her deeper into unladylike territory, and she's hired to solve a murder. Did gorgeous, landed Hamilton Garrett V really kill his mother twenty years ago? And if so, what is Sarah Booth doing falling for this possible murderer? When she asks one too many questions and a new corpse turns up, she is suddenly a suspect herself...and Sarah Booth finds that digging up the bones of the past could leave her rolling over in her grave.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1403183130i/905887.jpg", "genres": ["Audiobook", "Southern", "Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Paranormal", "Mystery Thriller", "Ghosts", "Romance", "Humor"], "asin": "0553581716", "isbn": "0553581716", "isbn13": "9780553581713", "publisher": "Bantam", "series": ["Sarah Booth Delaney"], "author": ["Carolyn Haines"], "publishDate": 941529600000, "characters": ["Sarah Booth Delaney"], "places": ["Mississippi", "Zinnia, Mississippi"], "ratingHistogram": [106, 228, 1349, 2347, 1815], "ratingsCount": 5845, "reviewsCount": 501, "numPages": 336, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Barry Award", "awardedAt": 946713600000, "category": "Best Paperback Original", "hasWon": null}]}
