{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/33440.Lemon_Meringue_Pie_Murder", "title": "Lemon Meringue Pie Murder", "titleComplete": "Lemon Meringue Pie Murder (Hannah Swensen, #4)", "description": "Hannah Swensen thought she'd finally discovered the recipe for a perfect life. But her sometime beau Norman Rhodes tosses a surprise ingredient into the mix when he phones to tell her he's just bought a house from local drugstore clerk Rhonda Scharf - which he plans to tear down in order to build the dream home he and Hannah designed. It seems the plan has been cooking for quite some time, and Hannah is shocked - especially since her ring finger is still very much bare. The good news is that the soon-to-be-torn-down house is full of antiques - and Norman has given Hannah and her mother first dibs. They uncover some gorgeous old furniture, a patchwork quilt ... and Rhonda Scharf's dead body. A little more sleuthing turns up the half-eaten remains of a very special dinner for two - and one of The Cookie Jar's famous lemon meringue pies. Now it's up to Hannah to turn up the heat - and get busy tracking down the clues. Starting in her very own kitchen.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388236161i/33440.jpg", "genres": ["Audiobook", "Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Mystery Thriller", "Chick Lit", "Adult", "Romance", "Crime", "Contemporary"], "asin": "0758215045", "isbn": "0758215045", "isbn13": "9780758215048", "publisher": "Kensington", "series": ["Hannah Swensen"], "author": ["Joanne Fluke"], "publishDate": 1072944000000, "characters": ["Hannah Swensen"], "places": ["Lake Eden, Minnesota", "Minnesota"], "ratingHistogram": [169, 886, 6241, 8141, 5620], "ratingsCount": 21057, "reviewsCount": 1202, "numPages": 348, "language": "English"}
