{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/13052351-gunpowder-plot", "title": "Gunpowder Plot", "titleComplete": "Gunpowder Plot (Daisy Dalrymple, #15)", "description": "Fatal Fireworks on Guy Fawkes Night...Daisy Darlymple is delighted to accept an invitation from her old school friend. Gwen Tyndall lives at Edge Manor in the Cotswolds and Daisy's visit will coincide with their annual fireworks display on 5th November. But this year, amid the festivities, Gwen's father and another man are found dead. It would appear that Sir Harold turned the gun on himself after shooting his guest.But could this apparent suicide be murder? After all, Sir Harold was notoriously bad tempered and there was no love lost between him and his children. And when Daisy and her husband uncover an explosive family secret , it soon becomes clear that a trigger-happy killer will go to any length to keep it hidden...Praise for the Daisy Dalrymple 'Cunning... appropriate historical detail and witty dialogue are the finishing touches on this engaging 1920s period piece.' - Publishers Weekly'As always, Dunn evokes the life and times of 1920s England while providing a plot that is a cut above the average British cosy. This will delight readers who love country-house mysteries.' - Booklist'For fans of Dorothy L. Sayers' novels' - Library Journal", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1350877448i/13052351.jpg", "genres": ["Audiobook", "Murder Mystery", "Cozy Mystery", "British Literature", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Historical", "Historical Fiction", "Historical Mystery", "Crime"], "asin": "B005G22WN0", "publisher": "Robinson", "series": ["Daisy Dalrymple"], "author": ["Carola Dunn"], "publishDate": 1312527600000, "ratingHistogram": [6, 75, 819, 1152, 557], "ratingsCount": 2609, "reviewsCount": 175, "numPages": 272, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/5726629-hush-my-mouth", "title": "Hush My Mouth", "titleComplete": "Hush My Mouth (Southern Fried Mystery #4)", "description": "Now that attorney Avery Andrews is back in town, business is booming. There\u2019s the team of ghost hunters who arrive at Avery\u2019s office one fine spring day, searching for ectoplasm from the long-dead. The ghosters are also having altercations with the locals (a raging biker gang and Avery\u2019s own P.I. among them) but Avery\u2019s got other \u201creal\u201d problems with the dearly departed: The twenty-year-old unsolved murder of Wenda Sims. Not long ago Wenda\u2019s niece, Neanna, came to Dacus looking for clues about what happened to her aunt. Then Neanna, too, went missing\u2026and was found dead. Now Neanna\u2019s best friend and adopted sister, Fran French, has come to town. Can Avery help Fran solve the two murders and prevent Fran from meeting the same fate? It\u2019s time for Avery to unearth the truth about the past before it comes back to haunt Dacus\u2026for good.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1316130960i/5726629.jpg", "genres": ["Southern", "Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Mystery Thriller"], "asin": "0312354436", "isbn": "0312354436", "isbn13": "9780312354435", "publisher": "Minotaur Books", "author": ["Cathy Pickens"], "publishDate": 1228204800000, "characters": ["Avery Andrews"], "places": ["Dacus, South Carolina"], "ratingHistogram": [14, 28, 123, 160, 152], "ratingsCount": 477, "reviewsCount": 40, "numPages": 304, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10389672-an-inconsiderate-death", "title": "An Inconsiderate Death", "titleComplete": "An Inconsiderate Death (Sukey Reynolds, #1)", "description": "The normally peaceful Gloucestershire village of Marsdean finds itself host to a murder scene. Lorraine Chant, wife of a wealthy businessman is found strangled in her home. On first inspection, the police suspect that she disturbed a burglar in her home and the thief panicked. But curiously, it seems that he knew about the two hidden safes at the Chant's house yet nothing was taken. Coincidentally, the Chants' handyman, Terry Holland, a man with a few secrets of his own, finds out that his van has been stolen and abandoned on the same day. Sukey is a police photographer and Scene of Crime Officer, who is helping to investigate the crime scene. Although she doesn't yet realise it, she has already met the murderer of Lorraine Chant. Hugo Bayliss is a man of many identities, dubious background and has a penchant for attractive married women, including Lorraine Chant. When he offers Sukey extra money to do some freelance photography, Sukey unwittingly becomes involved on the other side of crime.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1361107517i/10389672.jpg", "genres": ["Amazon", "Cozy Mystery", "British Literature", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Thriller", "Mystery Thriller", "Suspense", "Crime"], "asin": "0727852337", "isbn": "0727852337", "isbn13": "9780727852335", "publisher": "Severn House", "series": ["Sukey Reynolds"], "author": ["Betty Rowlands"], "publishDate": 878371200000, "ratingHistogram": [23, 63, 334, 764, 887], "ratingsCount": 2071, "reviewsCount": 115, "numPages": 256, "language": "English"}
