{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/20946006-the-making-of-matt", "title": "The Making of Matt", "titleComplete": "The Making of Matt (The Evolving Door #1)", "description": "The \u201cEvolving Door\u201d series details the heartwarming and often surprising transformations of the title characters as their lives are rocked by crisis and turmoil, often of their own making. The first book in the series, \u201cThe Making of Matt\u201d is the springboard for the rest of the books. Characters that the reader meets in \u201cMatt\u201d are featured in the other three books of this sexy, sweet and sometimes tragic romp through the human psyche.The Making of Matt \u2013 \u201cThe Making of Matt\u201d is a touching narrative which exposes the seamy underbelly of one man\u2019s transformation from wayward husband to soul-searching single and beyond. Its pages are steeped in the poignancy, awkwardness, despair, titillation and hope encompassed by real life, and the story presents the eyebrow-raising nitty-gritty of the male mind without shame or compromise. The evolution of the main character is one from which men can draw hope and encouragement, and about which women can breathe a sigh of heartfelt relief. You\u2019ll hate him, you\u2019ll love him, you\u2019ll laugh and cry for him, and eventually, you\u2019ll forgive him.", "publisher": "Amazon ", "author": ["Summer Prescott"], "publishDate": 1393574400000, "ratingHistogram": [0, 0, 0, 3, 8], "ratingsCount": 11, "reviewsCount": 6, "numPages": 322, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/41150387-terns-of-endearment", "title": "Terns of Endearment", "titleComplete": "Terns of Endearment (Meg Langslow, #25)", "description": " A new side-splitting Meg Langslow mystery from award-winning, New York Times bestselling author of Toucan Keep a Secret Meg's grandfather has been booked to give lectures on a cruise as part of the education/entertainment itinerary, and he's arranged for a passel of family members to join him.The passengers' vacation quickly becomes a nightmare when they wake up to find themselves broken down and in need of repairs. Things get even worse when a crew member announces to all that a woman has jumped overboard, leaving behind her shoes, shawl, and a note. The note reveals she's a disliked member of a writers' group onboard for a retreat, and the group is split on whether this is in-character for her.The captain decides not to investigate, saying he'll notify American authorities when they reach their destination. But Meg's father decides they need to look into whether there was possible foul play while the prime suspects are all stuck on board. It'll be a race against the clock to solve this mystery before they make the necessary repairs and return to shore.Donna Andrews' long-running Meg Langslow series continues to be beloved by its fans, who loyally buy every new installment. Terns of Endearment is a perfect new addition, full of laughter, adventure, and Andrews' wonderful cast of wacky characters.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1538394806i/41150387.jpg", "genres": ["Audiobook", "Amateur Sleuth", "Adult Fiction", "Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Mystery Thriller", "Humor", "Adult", "Contemporary"], "asin": "1250192978", "isbn": "1250192978", "isbn13": "9781250192974", "publisher": "Minotaur Books", "series": ["Meg Langslow"], "author": ["Donna Andrews"], "publishDate": 1565074800000, "ratingHistogram": [11, 64,