{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/22859799-murder-at-beechwood", "title": "Murder at Beechwood", "titleComplete": "Murder at Beechwood (Gilded Newport Mysteries #3)", "description": "For fans of HBO\u2019s The Gilded Age, explore the dark side of the alluring world of America\u2019s 19th century elite in this gripping series of riveting mysteries\u2026For Newport, Rhode Island\u2019s high society, the summer of 1896 brings lawn parties, sailboat races\u2026and murder. Having turned down the proposal of Derrick Andrews, Emma Cross has no imminent plans for matrimony\u2014let alone motherhood. But when she discovers an infant left on her doorstep, she naturally takes the child into her care. Using her influence as a cousin to the Vanderbilts and a society page reporter for the \n  Newport Observer\n, Emma launches a discreet search for the baby\u2019s mother. One of her first stops is a lawn party at Mrs. Caroline Astor\u2019s Beechwood estate. But an idyllic summer\u2019s day is soon clouded by tragedy. During a sailboat race, textile magnate Virgil Monroe falls overboard. There are prompt accusations of foul play\u2014and even Derrick Andrews falls under suspicion. Deepening the intrigue, a telltale slip of lace may link the abandoned child to the drowned man. But as Emma navigates dark undercurrents of scandalous indiscretions and violent passions, she\u2019ll need to watch her step to ensure that no one lowers the boom on her\u2026", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1413749110i/22859799.jpg", "genres": ["Amateur Sleuth", "Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Historical", "Mystery Thriller", "Historical Fiction", "Romance", "Historical Mystery", "Crime"], "asin": "0758290861", "isbn": "0758290861", "isbn13": "9780758290861", "publisher": "Kensington", "series": ["Gilded Newport Mysteries"], "author": ["Alyssa Maxwell"], "publishDate": 1432623600000, "ratingHistogram": [12, 49, 419, 955, 6