{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/16101141-murder-at-hatfield-house", "title": "Murder at Hatfield House", "titleComplete": "Murder at Hatfield House (Elizabethan Mysteries, #1)", "description": "FIRST IN A NEW SERIES!\n  1558. Kate Haywood, a simple musician in the employ of a princess, will find herself involved in games of crowns as she sets out to solve the murder of the queen\u2019s envoy....\n \u00a0 England is in tumult under the rule of Queen Mary and her Spanish husband. Confined to house arrest at Hatfield House, young Princess Elizabeth is the country\u2019s greatest hope. Far from court intrigues, Elizabeth finds solace in simple things: the quiet countryside and peaceful recreation, including the melodies of her chief musician and his daughter, Kate Haywood. \u00a0 But Kate will prove herself most valuable when an envoy of the queen\u2014sent to flush out heretics in the princess\u2019s household\u2014is found dead on the grounds of Hatfield. Acting as Elizabeth\u2019s eyes and ears, Kate is sent out on the trail of a killer whose mission could destroy her family, friends\u2014and the future of England.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1365986181i/16101141.jpg", "genres": ["Cozy Mystery", "British Literature", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Historical", "Mystery Thriller", "Tudor Period", "Elizabethan Period", "Historical Fiction", "Historical Mystery"], "asin": "0451415116", "isbn": "0451415116", "isbn13": "9780451415110", "publisher": "Berkley", "series": ["Elizabethan Mysteries"], "author": ["Amanda McCabe", "Amanda Carmack"], "publishDate": 1380610800000, "places": ["London, England"], "ratingHistogram": [8, 37, 155, 190, 108], "ratingsCount": 498, "reviewsCount": 88, "numPages": 288, "language": "English"}
