{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/24612181-flipped-for-murder", "title": "Flipped for Murder", "titleComplete": "Flipped for Murder (Country Store Mysteries, #1)", "description": "In this freshly baked series, author Maddie Day lifts the lid on a small town in southern Indiana, where a newcomer is cooking up a new start--until a murderer muddles the recipe...Nursing a broken heart, Robbie Jordan is trading in her life on the West Coast for the rolling hills of southern Indiana. After paying a visit to her Aunt Adele, she fell in love with the tiny town of South Lick. And when she spots a For Sale sign on a rundown country store, she decides to snap it up and put her skills as a cook and a carpenter to use. Everyone in town shows up for the grand re-opening of Pans \u2018n Pancakes, but when the mayor's disagreeable assistant is found dead, Robbie realizes that not all press is good press. With all eyes on her, she'll have to summon her puzzle-solving skills to clear her name, unscramble the town's darkest secrets, and track down a cold-blooded killer--before she's the next to die...", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1422811702i/24612181.jpg", "genres": ["Audiobook", "Food", "Adult Fiction", "Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Mystery Thriller", "Adult", "Crime", "Contemporary"], "asin": "1617739251", "isbn": "1617739251", "isbn13": "9781617739255", "publisher": "Kensington", "series": ["Country Store Mystery"], "author": ["Maddie Day", "Edith Maxwell"], "publishDate": 1445929200000, "places": ["Indiana"], "ratingHistogram": [51, 181, 1074, 1716, 1181], "ratingsCount": 4203, "reviewsCount": 551, "numPages": 304, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/31838340-acting-up", "title": "Acting Up", "titleComplete": "Acting Up (L.A. Lights #2)", "description": "Acting Up: More Adventures of a Hollywood Dog Walker is the third book in a series of new adult romantic comedies set in Tinseltown. Twenty-one-year-old Tessa Taylor has so much going for her: a loving relationship with Ryan, a burgeoning acting career, a profitable dog-walking business, and a fantastic group of friends. So why isn\u2019t she happy? For starters, she\u2019s been flopping at auditions, and Ryan isn\u2019t as supportive of her acting career as she\u2019d like him to be. When Tessa meets sexy, wild-boy rocker Ash Adams, she can\u2019t stop thinking about him, but is he the man she really needs? Meanwhile, her dog-walking business leads her to danger. She ends up playing a key part in breaking up a ruthless dognapping ring, culminating in a late-night mission to an abandoned asylum and a dramatic shootout in the LA River. With all these problems, can Tessa overcome the odds and find the happiness she yearns for? One thing\u2019s for sure: the constants in her life are fabulous friends and delightful dogs and the sidesplitting\u2014and sometimes perilous\u2014adventures they share.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1473047187i/31838340.jpg", "publisher": "Write from the Heart Publications", "series": ["L.A. Lights"], "author": ["Di Jones"], "publishDate": 1472972400000, "ratingHistogram": [0, 1, 2, 4, 11], "ratingsCount": 18, "reviewsCount": 14, "numPages": 229, "language": "English"}
