{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/26853389-the-calamity-caf", "title": "The Calamity Caf\u00e9", "titleComplete": "The Calamity Caf\u00e9 (Down South Caf\u00e9 Mystery, #1)", "description": "First in a new cozy mystery series featuring Southern cooking that is to die for.Aspiring chef and small-town Virginia native Amy Flowers is ready to open her own caf\u00e9 offering old-fashioned Southern food. But her dream may go up in smoke when someone kills the competition...Tired of waiting tables at Lou\u2019s Joint, Amy Flowers doesn\u2019t just quit\u2014she offers to buy the place from her bully of a boss, so she can finally open the caf\u00e9 of her dreams. Amy can't wait to serve the kind of Southern, down-home treats and dishes that her grandmother always loved to the kooky cast of regulars at the restaurant. She knows her comfort food will be the talk of the sweet, small town of Winter Garden, Virginia.At first Lou Lou refuses to sell, but when she seems ready to make a deal, she tells Amy to come see her. \u00a0Showing up at the eatery ready to negotiate, Amy is shocked to find her former employer murdered. As the prime suspect, Amy will have to clear her name by serving up the real killer\u2014and with Lou Lou\u2019s stack of enemies, that\u2019s a tall order.Includes delicious Southern recipes!", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1453058708i/26853389.jpg", "genres": ["Southern", "Food", "Adult Fiction", "Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Culinary", "Mystery Thriller", "Crime", "Contemporary"], "asin": "1101990783", "isbn": "1101990783", "isbn13": "9781101990780", "publisher": "Berkley", "series": ["Down South Caf\u00e9 Mystery "], "author": ["Gayle Leeson"], "publishDate": 1465282800000, "places": ["Virginia"], "ratingHistogram": [11, 51, 295, 478, 330], "ratingsCount": 1165, "reviewsCount": 220, "numPages": 283, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/31450618-gone-gull", "title": "Gone Gull", "titleComplete": "Gone Gull (Meg Langslow #21)", "description": "Andrews soars into summer with a crafty new Meg Langslow mystery.Gone Gull brings readers yet another knee-slapping adventure filled with New York Times bestselling author Donna Andrews\u2019 cast of wacky characters.Meg is spending the summer at the Biscuit Mountain Craft Center, helping her grandmother Cordelia run the studios. But someone is committing acts of vandalism, threatening to ruin the newly-opened center\u2019s reputation. Is it the work of a rival center? Have the developers who want to build a resort atop Biscuit Mountain found a new tactic to pressure Cordelia into selling? Or is the real target Meg\u2019s grandfather, who points out that any number of environmentally irresponsible people and organizations could have it in for him?While Meg is trying to track down the vandal, her grandfather is more interested in locating a rare gull. Their missions collide when a body is found in one of the classrooms. Can Meg identify the vandal and the murderer in time to save the center\u2019s name\u2014while helping her grandfather track down and rescue his beloved gulls?", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1481264733i/31450618.jpg", "genres": ["Audiobook", "Adult Fiction", "Cozy Mystery", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Mystery Thriller", "Humor", "Animals", "Adult", "Contemporary"], "asin": "1250078563", "isbn": "1250078563", "isbn13": "9781250078568", "publisher": "Minotaur Books", "series": ["Meg Langslow"], "author": ["Donna Andrews"], "publishDate": 1501570800000, "ratingHistogram": [13, 67, 595, 1117, 741], "ratingsCount": 2533, "reviewsCount": 303, "numPages": 304, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Lefty Award", "awardedAt": 1514793600000, "category": "Best Humorous Mystery Novel", "hasWon": null}]}
